text:
my brain is so full of things i want to write & share but it's scary putting my fingers to the keyboard when i don't know how it's going to turn out or whether people will relate to or even care about the things i have to say

i read audre lorde's your silence will not protect you recently & keep flicking back to highlighted paragraphs like this one

i think many of us can probably relate to this, can't we? we bottle things up because we're worried about what people will think of us or we're scared we'll make things worse. but in the long run, staying silent doesn't protect us from the very thing we're desperate to speak out against

here's a quote from chidera eggerue's what a time to be alone. i shared it a few months ago but i loved it so much & it's relevant here so i thought i'd share it again 😁 "to care is to be vulnerable. according to the world, it's not cool to be vulnerable; it's cool to be stoic, aloof and unconcerned, because to emotionally inept people, this shows resilience, strength of character and the oh-so-admirable quality of being eternally unbothered. but this is all wrong, because to be constantly 'unbothered' is to be dead inside

for a lot of people, caring means losing. these are the people who invest all their energy into performing instead of living, because to appear unbothered all the time, you must be in a constant state of pretence. don't aim to be like these people. they need more help than you think you do. but it is not your place to save them"

text: breanna stewart is a young wnba player, famously from uconn who is arguably the best in the league. she is viewed as a strong and confident 6’4 woman who dominates the game. it was a huge surprise to the public when stewart announced that she had been sexually abused as a child. she told her story to the world for the first time in the height of the #metoo movement. her story was eye opening and inspirational to women of all ages since she is so widely admired for breaking gender norms in her career. she recently partnered with rainn (rape, abuse & incest national network) to help survivors get the appropriate resources since she never went to therapy (theundefeated.com). #ecstorytellers

text:
true transformation in life happens when we are willing to really own our story.  there are pieces of our lives we would much rather keep hidden in a closet for no one to see.  it’s easier that way, because no one knows.  but is it really easier?
.
.
.
i used to think it was easier too. however, it wasn’t until i finally started talking about chapters in my life that i’d rather keep hidden that change started to occur.  it wasn’t until i realized my addiction to food stemmed from a lack of self love - me not believing i deserved happiness, health, and love.  it was me hiding behind the food, diet cokes and sweets when my emotions were out of control.  it wasn’t until i recognized that i turn to food when i’m anxious, embarrassed, stressed or scared that i was able to finally overcome it. .
.
.
it wasn’t until i shared about being taken advantage of by a boss, someone i aspired to be like, that i realized my toxic relationships also stemmed from a lack of self love.  i then put a plan in place to heal and learn what it feels like to speak my worth, claim my value, and be ok with making people uncomfortable by setting appropriate personal boundaries.
.
.
.
i’m not saying you need to share your story with the world. not at all. but i am telling you that if you truly want to change, heal, and finally reach those goals then you must be willing to explore what got you here.  sharing this in a sacred space built just for you and those on a similar journey is part of my calling.  i don’t take it lightly, and i also don’t take everyone in who asks because it’s more important to me that i protect who i do let in.
.
.
.
we are embarking on a deep journey in january centered around breaking the cycle of patterns you have both inherited and learned.  you’re going to understand why you have experienced trauma, sickness, obesity and sadness in your life - and how to heal.  the missing link to what you’ve tried before is the deeper dive into what got you here to begin with. .
.
today, reflect on the patterns you would like to change, and how important to you it really is to finally break that cycle.

text:
here’s a horror story for you: one time i invited a group of boys walking down hollywood blvd to come to my show that was down the street that night... because i did that, one of the boys took that as an invitation to go on my instagram and dm me asking me out. when i said i was flattered but not interested, he proceeded to comment that i was a slut on every single photo i had on instagram. after i blocked him, i started receiving email after email to my business account pretending to be from other people (however the email address was from his name) and continued harassing me. now, he’s finally blocked from everything i have, but this is not the first time something like this has happened to me (and it’s happened to many of my friends as well). so with that being said.... i’d like to express my support for all women in the entertainment industry and say that, you deserve to be able to market and promote your art in any way you so desire. for me, i choose to not let one shitty guy deter me from interacting face to face with people about my music and to not feel bad for dressing how i want to dress for shows, photos. etc. -

text:
jag tänker på bakslaget efter #metoo.  på hur utpekade män får sina jobb tillbaka och blir välkomnade med en ursäkt in i finrummen igen. medans kvinnor som vågade säga deras namn lämnas ute i kylan, avfärdade som hysteriska manshatare och kallas "mobbare". jag tänker på symbolvärdet i att en man som i sin egen självbiografi berättar om hur han utsatt kvinnor för sexuella övergrepp inbjuds av @svt att ringa in det nya året.

jag tänker också på symbolvärdet i att en rad kvinnor än en gång går ihop och säger ifrån. den oerhörda kraft det finns i det, i systerskap. i att det trots bakslaget är lite mindre tyst och lite mindre ensamt.

jag tänker även på hur lätt det är att som man komma undan om du inte namnges. "nej inte denna man". "inte jag". "inte han". i efterdyningarna ett år efter #metoo så har den stora debatten kommit att handla om "vart det gick fel " och vilka pressetiska regler som isidosatts. jag kan se värdet i att de etablerade nyhetsmedierna tänker över sina beslut och att de ansvariga utgivarna där får stå till svars. samtidigt får dessa publiceringar inte blandas ihop med att enskilda kvinnor valde att ta bladet från munnen och namnge sina förövare. för samtidigt som pressetiken kan diskuteras  så ser jag ett värde i att peka ut. att kvinnor ställer sig upp och inte bara säger "jag har blivit utsatt" utan även "han utsatte mig". vi behöver prata om strukturer. vi behöver prata om "alla män". men så länge patriarkatet lever behöver vi även peka ut de män på toppen som gång efter gång, år efter år, kränker och begår övergrepp. så länge vi inte säger deras namn kan de trots #metoo annars fortsätta relativt ostört. …...........................…...…….........….............................
bilder, kontext och allmänt jävlaranamma är hämtat och finns att finna hos @elaineeksvard @cissiwallin och @miaskaringerlazar

text:
asia argento en camarilla: "pasé un año de mierda"
explicación: invitada por "clique dimanche" en canal +, la actriz italiana describió como "gesto kamikaze" su discurso anti weinstein en el último festival de cine de cannes. y se molestó rápidamente cuando se le preguntó sobre los cargos de agresión sexual de jimmy bennet.

meses que no habíamos visto en la televisión francesa. desde mayo y su poderoso discurso en la ceremonia de clausura del último festival de cine de cannes. asia argento fue el domingo 9 de diciembre, invitada de "clique dimanche" junto a su amigo nicolas sirkis, líder del grupo de indochina para quien dirigió el video de "la vie est belle". el dúo comienza hablando de sus proyectos artísticos conjuntos y luego evoca la crisis de los chalecos amarillos y el movimiento de 5 estrellas en italia. 
asia argento se cuestiona en este discurso que marcó los espíritus en la croisette y en otros lugares. "en 1997, fui violada aquí por harvey weinstein", dijo a una audiencia atónita. ella habla de ello hoy como un "kamikaze, gesto suicida". ella dice que "no fue idea suya contar lo que sucedió con weinstein, fue el reportero quien me llamó porque sabía que ya había hecho una película sobre ella cuando tenía 23 años ". más tarde castigó el punto de inflexión de los movimientos #metoo y time's up. "se convirtió en algo muy importante de lo que hollywood se trataba, se convirtió en una franquicia, un alfiler en la alfombra roja".
#asiaargento #nicolasirkis #cliquedimanche #interview

meses que no habíamos visto en la televisión francesa. desde mayo y su poderoso discurso en la ceremonia de clausura del último festival de cine de cannes. asia argento fue el domingo 9 de diciembre, invitada de "clique dimanche" junto a su amigo nicolas sirkis, líder del grupo de indochina para quien dirigió el video de "la vie est belle". el dúo comienza hablando de sus proyectos artísticos conjuntos y luego evoca la crisis de los chalecos amarillos y el movimiento de 5 estrellas en italia. 
asia argento se cuestiona en este discurso que marcó los espíritus en la croisette y en otros lugares. "en 1997, fui violada aquí por harvey weinstein", dijo a una audiencia atónita. ella habla de ello hoy como un "kamikaze, gesto suicida". ella dice que "no fue idea suya contar lo que sucedió con weinstein, fue el reportero quien me llamó porque sabía que ya había hecho una película sobre ella cuando tenía 23 años ". más tarde castigó el punto de inflexión de los movimientos #metoo y time's up. "se convirtió en algo muy importante de lo que hollywood se trataba, se convirtió en una franquicia, un alfiler en la alfombra roja".
#asiaargento #nicolasirkis #cliquedimanche #interview

text:
@tazzdavies91 originally posted this quote. follow her if you love this one cos she seriously sources the best quotes on her feed.

anyway this quote struck me because i was previously in an abusive relationship with someone who literally tried to beat the madness out of me. whenever i was acting like my crazy self i would pay for it. at the time i playfully ran away and thought it was a game. i was young and even the bruises i was left with weren't enough to keep me away. today i am in a loving relationship with a man who lets me be myself, even if it's a little too much for him. he sometimes gets annoyed but has never once laid a hand on me in over 11 years together. it really is a blessing from the universe that i found someone who can let me be myself and i am so grateful. the need to get married and have kids is often what is fed to us to look for in a relationship. for me i would rather have what i do right now than a family with a man who won't let me be me.

quote reads: fall in love with someone who enjoys your madness, not an idiot who forces you to be normal.

text:
long post alert!! when i released my debut book on 15th november this year it was a total dream come true and the culmination of 18 months work.
it wasn't written to show off, blame or criticise anyone, but to show its readers that they too could overcome any adversity they faced in their lives.
my book went to number 1 in an hour after it was released and i was overwhelmed to have had such amazing and generous feedback from so many people, including the talented and inspiring crew at @authors&co.
i felt totally on top of the world and on purpose. through my challenges i was able to leave other's inspired and in a better place, and this was my sole intention. 
on the monday the hate began from a few members of my closest family calling me a liar,  quibbling over dates and accusing me of being cruel and using my story to enhance my business interests. more over they then began to mention legal action and this stopped me in my tracks. 
it fucking terrified me and i felt totaly lost. 
having thought i was strong and  healed i was shocked at how sad, desolate and distraught i was. 
i didn't care that they called me a liar. i know my truth. i know all that happened to me and i know that i wrote my story from my perspective.
i knew that i wasn't being vindictive nor malicious yet was aware that my book would have upset some people who didn't share my views of people i wrote about, because frankly their experiences and relationships with them were so totally opposing to my own but i wrote my truth from the heart. 
i have never had anxiety but i guess this is what i had.
i  felt sick, couldnt eat, shook, over thought, cried and had a chronic fear of being alone.
in order to preserve my sanity i took my book off sale and hid for a week, crying and weak.
the love of my friends and husband got me through that week and i gave myself time to heal.
i considered why i had shared my story and what i wanted from it.
it wasnt money, fame or infamy. what i wanted was to inspire, empower and motivate you to believe in you and your future, in your potential.
so, its no secret is back tomorrow!
#warrior #survivors #metoo #endviolenceagainstwomenandgirls #memoir #writersofinstagram

text:
#metoo 
a terrified 11 year old amybeth feels she is now ready to share her story.
-
-
in a convenience store, in london. 
i was 11 years old the first time a man exposed himself to me behind the cash register on the counter.. while my own granddad stood beside me unaware of the horrific things this man was doing.
i was confused, i thought he had an itch.. his smile was sinister but i was young.
he was never caught. he ran like the coward that he was.
i thought something like that could never happen again.
-
-
i've been slut shamed, cat called, even grabbed multiple times since then, and every time it happens it becomes less of a big deal.
i began to be told that things like that are to be expected as i get older and that's just the way the world is.
how about no?
how about 
it's not what you wear
it's not about the strength you could've used to fight them off
it's not about if you said no.. it's about if you didn't say yes
it's not how you act
it's not how much alcohol you consume
it's not the way the world is
it's not your fault.
-
-
you do not need to come forward with your stories to stand with us in this discussion.
-
-
we all stand together in solidarity.
(i apologize for the photo.. it's all i have at the moment)

text: this is a reality post. while i am trying really hard to be less angry and negative, some days it takes all my energy to get out of bed and make sure i eat. while other days i do my makeup, put cute outfits on, and have laughing photo shoots with my friends. some days i am the happiest, most motivated person i know. other days i win when i make it to work. those are the days when it feels impossible to smile or see a way out. those are the days i don’t post anything because i use this page as a way to heal and share my thoughts, opinions, and experiences. however i’ve been feeling the importance of more people posting there real struggles, the good and the bad because not one person can go through life with no bad days. social media has so many benefits, but i believe one of the biggest consequences is the fomo we often experience. as much as bad days suck they will happen and they do happen to everyone. you are never alone. there is nothing wrong with you because of your struggles. you are human💕 #metoo #believesurvivors #believewomen #politics #wait #dontgiveup #mystory #sumasopinion #weneedchange #ivoted #ladygang #iamawoman #iam #notyourfault #ptsd #iwill #stronger #survivor #metoomeredith #ladylike #superwoman #youcandoit #healing #feminist #feminism #equality #youareloved #youarehuman #youareenough #perserverance

text:
hannah is a force to be reckoned with: she is a globally celebrated comedian, writer, producer, and social justice warrior. her brilliant 2018 netflix series and live shows nanette won public and critical acclaim, both at home in australia, and abroad.

hannah is a passionate advocate for a number of causes, being active within lgbtqi advocacy and with organisations including the sacred heart mission. she recognises the importance of an intersectional lens in the perpetuation of privilege and disadvantage; and urges people to look beyond their own experience to unpack the role of gender, sexual identity, disability, and ethnicity in discrimination and abuse. 
this week, hannah delivered an incredibly powerful monologue on “good men” and misogyny as a speaker at the hollywood reporter's 2018 women in entertainment gala breakfast. if you haven’t watched it yet – please do! https://youtu.be/oepsqflhhbc

#hearmetoo #orangetheworld #16days #16daysofactivism #believesurvivors #unwomen #metoo #timesup #genderequality #activists #activism #gamechangers #changemakers

text:
this is not consent. 
as part of my senior show, the unspoken: voices of the voiceless, i did a performance piece regarding sexual assault. clothing is never an indication of consent to having sex. this is a social critique of victim blaming and the declaration that rape is justifiable dependent on the clothing worn during the assault.  no matter what an individual wears, they should never be subjected to rape, nor should they feel obligated to have sex.

in ireland, a 17 year old girl had her underwear used in a rape case with cousel saying "you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front." during this performance, i wore underwear that matched this description. 
this needs to stop. 
#thisisnotconsent #dontfuckingtouchme #metoo #timesup #sexualassaultsurvivor #sexualassault #nomeansno #violenceagainstwomen #endrapeculture #stopviolence #mybodymychoice

text:
velveteen buffalo is here to open eyes to the shared humanity within us all.
velveteen buffalo was created to serve as a reminder that we are all human.
that, yes, we all have unique differences, and it is these uniquenesses that unite us.
creating one species,
humanity.
yes, we are different on the surface and even in thought, but never forget that 
people are people. 
we all bleed red.

text:
hello and welcome new friends and followers! i’m so happy to get to know you here on instagram!
🖤 i’d like to take this opportunity to tell you a little about myself and my work. i’m a thirty-something texas girl with a passion for the written word and all forms of art and creativity.
🖤 i currently have four books available on amazon. the first three books of my new adult, paranormal romance series, the kiss series. (the faithful kiss, the possessive kiss, a kiss of betrayal). as well as a poetry book, insomnia.
🖤 for the kiss series i have three more books in the works to complete the series.
🖤 this year for nanowrimo i wrote another new adult romance called friendzone. it’s a friends-to-lovers story inspired loosely by people and events in my own life.
🖤 my latest project is called “#metoo: a collection of true story crimes against women.”
the book will be a collection of true story experiences written in women’s own words. these poems and stories will chronicle the crimes and the effects that the experiences had on each woman.
🔜 stories and poems will be accepted until december 31, 2018.
if you have a story/poem that you would like to include email me at mchillstromauthor@yahoo.com.
all stories/poems will be listed as anonymous submissions.
➡️the types of stories i am looking for include personal experiences of:
-sexual harassment -rape/assault -sexual, emotional, or physical abuse
-stalking
-gender discrimination
-i will accept other topics if they fit in with the theme as well.
🔴 through writing about my own experiences i have found peace and strength.
i hope others will find this as well and that the future readers of this collection will find courage and strength in the knowledge that they are not alone.
💲 proceeds from the sales of this collection will be donated to help sexual assault survivors.
🖤 to learn more about me and my work check out my website michellechillstromauthor.com

thank you again for following me!
.
.

text: trayvon benjamin martin, born february 5th, 1995, was a young black american. he is the catalyst and icon of the 21st century human rights movement. throughout history, young black americans and their fight for human and civil rights, have been the only obstacles consistently preventing america from becoming the worst of herself. the only vehicles keeping the “dream” of america alive. we are the living conscious of america. in a time when we fell asleep, while things were becoming worse than ever, this young black man’s sacrifice placed young black americans back on the front lines, picking up the ball where our predecessors left off. because of his sacrifice, because of the courage of young black americans, our gay community was encouraged to pick up and intensify their fight. our trans community were able to intensify their fight, our women were given the courage to resume their fight. throughout time, the blood and sacrifice of young black americans has willed america’s progress and served as the foundation for all human and civil rights causes to receive justice...yet 400 yrs later there is still no justice for us. thank you, #trayvonmartin ...for waking us up. you are the #emmetttill of the 21st century. ✊🏾#blackmen #blackwomen #blackpower #revolution #humanrights #civilrights #blacklivesmatter #lgbtq🌈 #womenempowerment #metoo #educateorganizepowertothepeople #elpoderalagente #ootd #justice #womensmarch #igdaily #igers

this is how russians travel from earth to saturn !!! through dimensional portals... in 2015 nasa researchers disclosed the truth about time travel and dimensional portals. there are places all over the universe we can travel to in an instant, using energetic portals in space, and the use of our consciousness.
the proof is indeed mounting that there are portals to other worlds. though the documentation is still ‘sketchy’! apparently, tesla too was obsessed with time travel. he worked on a time machine and reportedly succeeded, saying: ‘i could see the past, present and future all at the same time.’ tesla’s time travel experiment: i could see the past, present and future all at the same time’

tesla had claimed to have invented a powerful particle-beam weapon, known as the “death ray,” that could have proved invaluable in the ongoing conflict. so rather than risk tesla’s technology falling into the hands of america’s enemies, the government swooped in and took possession of all the property and documents from his room at the new yorker hotel.
what happened to tesla’s files from there, as well as what exactly was in those files, remains shrouded in mystery—and ripe for conspiracy theories. the fbi has finally declassified its files on nikola tesla, but questions remain.

after nikola tesla was found dead in january 1943 in his hotel room in new york city, representatives of the u.s. government’s office of alien property seized many documents relating to the brilliant and prolific 86-year-old inventor’s work.

technology (mit) was tasked with evaluating his papers to determine whether they contained “any ideas of significant value.” according to the declassified files,🔥dr. john g. trump🔥reported that his analysis showed tesla’s efforts to be “primarily of a speculative, philosophical and promotional character” and said the papers did “not include new sound, workable principles or methods for realizing such results.

this is how russians travel from earth to saturn !!! through dimensional portals... in 2015 nasa researchers disclosed the truth about time travel and dimensional portals. there are places all over the universe we can travel to in an instant, using energetic portals in space, and the use of our consciousness.
the proof is indeed mounting that there are portals to other worlds. though the documentation is still ‘sketchy’! apparently, tesla too was obsessed with time travel. he worked on a time machine and reportedly succeeded, saying: ‘i could see the past, present and future all at the same time.’ tesla’s time travel experiment: i could see the past, present and future all at the same time’

tesla had claimed to have invented a powerful particle-beam weapon, known as the “death ray,” that could have proved invaluable in the ongoing conflict. so rather than risk tesla’s technology falling into the hands of america’s enemies, the government swooped in and took possession of all the property and documents from his room at the new yorker hotel.
what happened to tesla’s files from there, as well as what exactly was in those files, remains shrouded in mystery—and ripe for conspiracy theories. the fbi has finally declassified its files on nikola tesla, but questions remain.

after nikola tesla was found dead in january 1943 in his hotel room in new york city, representatives of the u.s. government’s office of alien property seized many documents relating to the brilliant and prolific 86-year-old inventor’s work.

technology (mit) was tasked with evaluating his papers to determine whether they contained “any ideas of significant value.” according to the declassified files,🔥dr. john g. trump🔥reported that his analysis showed tesla’s efforts to be “primarily of a speculative, philosophical and promotional character” and said the papers did “not include new sound, workable principles or methods for realizing such results.

text:
this is how russians travel from earth to saturn !!! through dimensional portals... in 2015 nasa researchers disclosed the truth about time travel and dimensional portals. there are places all over the universe we can travel to in an instant, using energetic portals in space, and the use of our consciousness.
the proof is indeed mounting that there are portals to other worlds. though the documentation is still ‘sketchy’! apparently, tesla too was obsessed with time travel. he worked on a time machine and reportedly succeeded, saying: ‘i could see the past, present and future all at the same time.’ tesla’s time travel experiment: i could see the past, present and future all at the same time’

tesla had claimed to have invented a powerful particle-beam weapon, known as the “death ray,” that could have proved invaluable in the ongoing conflict. so rather than risk tesla’s technology falling into the hands of america’s enemies, the government swooped in and took possession of all the property and documents from his room at the new yorker hotel.
what happened to tesla’s files from there, as well as what exactly was in those files, remains shrouded in mystery—and ripe for conspiracy theories. the fbi has finally declassified its files on nikola tesla, but questions remain.

technology (mit) was tasked with evaluating his papers to determine whether they contained “any ideas of significant value.” according to the declassified files,🔥dr. john g. trump🔥reported that his analysis showed tesla’s efforts to be “primarily of a speculative, philosophical and promotional character” and said the papers did “not include new sound, workable principles or methods for realizing such results.

text: “clutch” here are some detail shots her face i thought it would be nice to share with you. (some info from previous post-“clutch” (life sized) from the avian show a few years ago. in her lap there is a little pile of bird skulls on a sheepskin. the skulls have been stained and gilded with metal leaf so they seem like a pile of dark jewels that she is playing with, fondling and perhaps protecting. her clutch of eggs. i see her as an expression of maternal and erotic self possession. i made her before the heat of the #metoo movement was on, and i have been thinking a lot about how to speak again about women and sexuality in this new cultural context. what has changed in me, in us, and all around us? i can feel my new work beginning to answer this call.... )#avian #ceramicsculpture #figurativeart #figuresculpture #contemporaryart #sculpture #birdskulls #skull #avianart #beautifulbizarre #clay

text: does this tervis tumbler offend you? i hope not. apparently, a few radio stations have pulled this classic christmas song from their holiday rotation because it sounds “rapey” (is that even a word?). what are we turning into as a nation when we concern ourselves with a fluff pop  song written in 1944 while there are many more pressing issues we’re facing? i understand the #metoo movement, and i support what they are trying to accomplish, but this is ridiculously overreaching and might prove harmful to their message if they want to be taken seriously. all the lady agrees to at the end of the song is another drink. but so what? have you heard some of the crap that’s on the radio these days? why is it easier to pick on an old song? instead of banning it outright, one radio station conducted a poll asking their listeners if they should remove the tune. 91% said to keep playing it. last time i checked, we live in a democracy where majority rules, so there you go. in the meantime, i’m going to toast to the holiday season with my tervis tumbler filled with hot chocolate, and i’ll ask my wife if she’d like some too, because baby, it’s cold outside.

this is how russians travel from earth to saturn !!! through dimensional portals... in 2015 nasa researchers disclosed the truth about time travel and dimensional portals. there are places all over the universe we can travel to in an instant, using energetic portals in space, and the use of our consciousness.
the proof is indeed mounting that there are portals to other worlds. though the documentation is still ‘sketchy’! apparently, tesla too was obsessed with time travel. he worked on a time machine and reportedly succeeded, saying: ‘i could see the past, present and future all at the same time.’ tesla’s time travel experiment: i could see the past, present and future all at the same time’

tesla had claimed to have invented a powerful particle-beam weapon, known as the “death ray,” that could have proved invaluable in the ongoing conflict. so rather than risk tesla’s technology falling into the hands of america’s enemies, the government swooped in and took possession of all the property and documents from his room at the new yorker hotel.
what happened to tesla’s files from there, as well as what exactly was in those files, remains shrouded in mystery—and ripe for conspiracy theories. the fbi has finally declassified its files on nikola tesla, but questions remain.

after nikola tesla was found dead in january 1943 in his hotel room in new york city, representatives of the u.s. government’s office of alien property seized many documents relating to the brilliant and prolific 86-year-old inventor’s work.

technology (mit) was tasked with evaluating his papers to determine whether they contained “any ideas of significant value.” according to the declassified files,🔥dr. john g. trump🔥reported that his analysis showed tesla’s efforts to be “primarily of a speculative, philosophical and promotional character” and said the papers did “not include new sound, workable principles or methods for realizing such results.

text:
i wish words like "gay", "straight", "male", "female", "black", or "white" didn't exist when referring to creatures. how about we replace those words with one, "living". i hate that when talking about some of my friends i have to say "my gay friends" or "they're also gay". or anything like that, why for some people do i need to specify what gender they prefer to love? or if they love any gender? or if they love both? can't i just say "yeah, this is my friend, they're a nice person, they keep on living like the rest of us, despite the harsh route "god" has sent all of us down. but hey, nobody said the road to happiness was easy. the most we can do is try." if you're triggered by me putting god in quotes it's just cause not everyone believes in him and there's no real way to know that's actually the name of whatever's up there. i try not to side with any religion in my posts because i honestly don't follow the rules of just one. if you wanna rant to me about how me saying god may not be real at all please do so privately so it doesn't disturb others but do keep in mind i will be reporting you if anything you say becomes violent at any point. 
looked into #metoo cause i was curious as to what people actually put there. it's exactly what i expected. people telling their stories and stuff like that. some were sad, i won't deny it but a lot of the posts were kinda random. 
the picture is my lock screen right now! i'll be changing it to rainbow soon though cause black and white is kinda boring after a bit.

text:
⤩
my truth 
was buried alive
it's no wonder
when you touch me
i cannot breathe
.
touch is such a beautiful & necessary expression of love. i'm tired of my body feeling like a battlefield.
it is difficult retraining these perceptions. i'm becoming more aware of the resistance in my physical form; mainly concerning touch. intellectually, i know that not all forms of human touch are of sexual nature, yet instinctually my body recoils or resists if anyone, even friends, simply try to hold my hand, rub my shoulders or even hug me. there is a moment that i freeze up or tremble, feeling familiar fight or flight adrenaline & my midwest mentality races to find a way to reject it politely. this fear doesn't really feel like "me" in the moment.. but an animal defense mechanism. how prey must feel. i take a moment to breathe and try to tell my body it is safe & to melt into it. sometimes i do, sometimes i don't. i know i'm not alone in this, i know women who have similar experiences.
regardless of gender, we all have a story. #metoo
it's tricky digging out these tender, tangled roots in my system and planting new seeds when i'm so far from the arms of the ones who make me feel safe, [♡] but out here there is no tip-toeing to my core.. or testing the warmth of the water.
i'll hold close my courage.
& jump.
.
.

text:

text:
scroll 👉👉👉👉
i recently answered a dm where someone wasn’t sure if their partner was a narcissist. i’m not a therapist, i don’t know these people and i certainly am not qualified to diagnose anyone—even if i were, again, i haven’t met them! (although in certain circumstances personal experience > education and i certainly think no one can truly talk about what narcissistic abuse does to someone at a certain level unless they’ve personally experienced the hell that is being involved with someone like this.) .
.
with all of this being said, unfairly labeling someone isn’t cool either!! it’s hurtful and insulting to call someone bipolar, another anorexic, someone else emotionally disregulated and another person clinically depressed when they aren’t. well it’s rude to label someone as npd when they aren’t either!! it isn’t fair to the person being labeled and it takes away from the true, awful abuse that victims experience from actual narcissists. know the signs. .
.
someone who takes a lot of selfies isn’t narcissistic in a lot of cases. maybe he/she is comfortable with who they are? maybe we could take self love lessons from them! another who talks about only themselves isn’t necessarily one either! maybe they’re nervous and not good at speaking to groups so they talk about what they know—themselves! .
.
stop labeling unless you know. and if you’re not sure, educate yourself, read several different reliable sources, talk to fighters/survivors, make a list if you have to. incorrectly labeling someone is not fair nor is it right!

text: ”men du fick väl betalt?”. det ekar i huvudet ibland. ”du fick väl betalt?” ”du fick väl betalt?!” ”men du fick betalt?”. jo visst fan fick jag betalt. när jag säljer sex får jag betalt, såklart. men att få betalt för ”sex” är som att få ett skadestånd innan övergreppet istället för efter. ett våldtäktsoffer (kanske) får skadestånd efteråt. en hora som jag får pengarna först. och då är inte det öht i närheten av den summa som betalas ut efter våldtäkt. ibland får jag bara 100kr, ibland får jag 1000kr. om jag går med på att ”ha sex” med någon för pengar, så betyder det att jag går med på det för pengar. jag tror att många känner igen sig i att ”ha sex” man inte vill ha pga det leder till något annat man vill ha. kanske pengar, kanske bekräftelse, kanske trygghet, kanske en bättre stämning. osv. jag tror att många kan relatera till att ”ställa upp på sex”. att betala någon för sex är att betala skadestånd för våldtäkt innan våldtäkten sker. man kan betala för någons samtycke men man kan aldrig med pengar komma ifrån att ett samtycke bara är ett samtycke när det är genuint. att ha sex med någon betyder att båda har sex med varandra. om den ena bara ligger där och härdar ut av olika orsaker så är det ett övergrepp. sex är ingen affärsuppgörelse. sex är inte att säga ja när man vill säga nej. sex är inte att bli vidrörd när man bara tillåter det pga pengar. det finns många personer som ändrar sitt nej till ett ja pga mutor. jag är en av dom. att säga ”nej jag vill inte ha sex med dig” betyder precis det. om torsken säger ”du får 1000kr om jag får ha sex med dig!” och jag då säger ”okej då”, så handlar det om att jag behöver pengar. inte i detta eller i något parallellt universum betyder ett nej ett ja. ett nej till sex är ett nej till sex. ett ja till pengar är inte ett ja till sex. (sexköp är ett bötesbrott, lägre böter än graffiti) #prostitution #utanskyddsnät #intedinhora #metoo
name: SEXKÖP ÄR ÖVERGREPP

text:

⠀
this all goes along with our orgysmic's new mission: we want to promote sexual health, fight discrimination and stigma based on sexual preferences, behaviours, phantasies, prejudices or identities, and defend sexual liberty! orgysmic is by and for lgbtipqs, kinksters, polys, people living with hiv, people of all sizes, sluts, asexuals, #metoo, sex workers, sexually active people with disabilities, sexually active elderly people, and poc! orgysmic is for you!⠀
⠀
and starting in one week, if you share our mission, you can support us on patreon and get awesome gifts in return! you'll be an integral part of orgysmic's success and on our way moving forward! so stay tuned for december 16th! ⠀
⠀

text:
copies of garden, our self-printed booklet of #poems and #illustrations inspired by and written for #survivors of abuse, rape and trauma will be available in exchange for donations on tuesday 11th at the christmas fayre, eldon building, university of portsmouth.

garden has received an excellent review here https://theeldonreview.wordpress.com/2018/12/02/review-of-garden-by-anna-and-tessa-foley/

excerpt here: the inclusion of enchanting pictures alongside the poems rescues some beauty from pain. these are visual metaphors for the identities of survivors who will not allow their victimhood to define them. the poem ‘you’ uses this conceit in a particularly moving way, its tone of ambiguity about whether the damage done is lasting – ‘you walk a stride each day and night’ – counterposed by the picture of a gorgeous flower.

all proceeds will go to portsmouth abuse and rape counselling service. 
#metoo #timesup #yourvoicematters #sexualabuse #domesticabuse  #rapesurvivor #portsmouth #poetry

text:
the #metoo movement began in 2017, which encouraged women who had experienced sexual assault or sexual harassment to come forward with their experiences on social media to showcase how common this experience is. this particular social media movement resulted in an overwhelming increase in dialogue about this issue. this image reflects the empowerment women felt as they were invited to share their experiences of sexual harassment or assault without the traditional stigma attached to it. 
negar mottahedah attempts to explain the origin of the hashtag in his book #iranelection: hashtag solidarity and the transformation of online life. he says the hashtag was used “as a way to create groups, the hashtag became an aggregator, a way to research a topic, and by bringing focus and attention to posted content, a way to measure the range and popularity of a topic on the social media platform.” although she was not the first to use the hashtag, alyssa milano popularized #metoo on twitter, leading to the viral campaign. this practice of hashtag activism gave women a sense of belonging, and attempted to make the discussion of sexual assault and harassment normal through empowerment. 
mottahedah described the connection formed on twitter through hashtags as an “emergence of [a] shared revolutionary consciousness”, which i think described the general attitude of the #metoo movement (pg 31). the women who participated in the hashtag were building a revolutionary consciousness surrounding an issue which was largely concealed in the past. this image depicts a woman using a megaphone to shout #metoo, which i think is an appropriate analogy to how the #metoo movement exploded online.

#militarizationandrebellioninthevisualsphere #citizenjournalism #hashtagactivism #metoo
#visualculturecarolinafall2018

@visualculturecarolina

text:
i normally do not get political on social media nor do i feel being passive aggressive on such platforms helps my case but something needs to be said so allow me to be a smidge hypocritical for a couple of minutes. 
i saw a post today that i disagree with wholeheartedly. some of you know the reason and others will find out when it’s the right time but i have a huge problem with the assumption that sexual crimes happen because a person looks a certain way. i understand it to be very different. rape never happens for a reason, other than the psycho doing it lacking empathy, morality and a respect for other people who are (more often than not) in your life. to blame what happens on the victim, for any reason, is wrong. nobody asks for this. #metoo

text:
when you move through those initial shakes and stand strong with others, there’s nothing like it...
.
.
.
i founded rising up because after an attack by a stranger, i found that, while rock climbing, my legs trembled as i attempted power moves on the rocks, and this was a sign of power, not weakness...
.
.
.
i spent years traveling the country in a van, only rock climbing. after that, i moved to hawaii and took up paddle boarding...
.
.
.
with both climbing and paddle boarding, you use power moves  to move through body shakes into stability, while those around you celebrate your strength...
.
.
.
it’s powerful! we bring people out every night, to dolphins, the sunset, the tropical sea air, and waves to master the act of moving forward in the face of life’s waves...
.
.
.
come paddle with us! we’re here with people from all over the globe every night rising up together!
.
.
.

text:
#metoo 😞
i feel ya girl.
.
remember when the whole “me too” movement began and it felt like there was finally a safe space to speak out? you felt less alone and realized you were actually supported.
.
you emerged from the shadows to join the ranks of countless women who were in a similar position.
.
but then time passed and things got pushed under the rug again.
.
maybe you spoke up to some people, felt free and had a momentary release... but then it was over.
.
you returned to carrying the burden, the guilt, and the shame.
.
it seemed like it was just expected of you to move on with ease.
.
“well you got it off your chest (no pun intended) so now it’s back to normal, right?” -says someone whose never experienced it.
.
wrong!!
.
things don’t just magically disappear like that. 🙅🏼‍♀️
.
negative energy around trauma and a deep loss of control/privacy doesn’t just float away into the clouds.
.
you have to do more.
.
that was just the first step - and a huge, inspiring, powerful one at that - but the journey to freedom takes more.
. . .
last week i opened up on a podcast about sexual assault and how i was stuck in some negative patterns.
.
i didn’t feel worthy enough to deserve better and i definitely didn’t feel strong enough to speak up or tell people to stop treating me that way.
.
looking back i can see the error of my ways, and how i was playing small. and when you play small - it can be easy to become a target.
.
in no way am i blaming myself or blaming women in these situations - but i have come to see the power i could’ve had if i’d truly believed in myself back then. we are all so much stronger than we know!
.
i can’t wait for you to hear my podcast interview (coming soon!) but until then i’m going to be using the next few posts to share some of my story and the things i learned through sexual assault.
.
i’m here with ya girl, i know the pain you’re carrying, the negative energy you’ve got bottled up inside.
.
and i’m here to help you release it. please shoot me a dm if you want my help. i’ve helped multiple clients work through their own sexual assaults and find freedom and clarity. and i’d love to help you do the same 🙏🏼💕
name: Release Expert & Energy Healer

text: i have a little story to tell about an experience at the #capetown7s this weekend. i was walking out of the stadium on my way to buy a drink when a guy decided it would be fun for him to stick his hand up my shorts.  i walked on for a few seconds before deciding, fuck this- this has happened one too many times and i am done with putting up with this bullshit. so i turned around and chased after the guy. grabbed him by the neck of his shirt, spun him around (the shirt ripped) and slapped him so hard his glasses flew off his face and i had an imprint of them on my hand for 30 minutes after. it was the best feeling of my life. i’m not proud that i resorted to violence, but i can tell you this, that fucker will think twice before he ever does that again. and the girls that watched it happen will hopefully be inspired to stop this bullshit. enough is enough. my only regret is that i didn’t pull a fist, because @boxing_wth_richardmakore has left me with a killer right hook and i would have left him sleeping. #metoo #enough #fightback.

text: for too many years now it has happened. purchase, use, replace. what am i talking about you ask? i’m talking about care abuse. many of you will be familiar with the #metoo campaign but now i am proud to stand behind a new campaign. one that represents cars and their rights. the #me3 campaign has been developed by yours truely to help give those cars affect a platform on which to express themselves. it will help them connect with other cars who have had their lives changed by car abuse and give them the opportunity to support each other. with this hashtag placed on any post you will see those who have been hurt and had their livelihoods destroyed by car abuse. car abuse affects 50% of all cars. it can be as simple as not cleaning it for weeks. one of the most extreme cases of car abuse which goes against every right a car is entitled to are car derby’s. this is when many cars are thrown into an arena and are forced to kill each other, with only one car surviving this oil bath. the #me3 campaign has already started petitioning for bans on these events and with your support more can be done to end this vicious excuses for entertainment. cars are often tossed into these events after they have reached their usefulness to their owner. they aren’t the newest model anymore and have been replaced by a smarter, better looking car. this hurts cars to see happen. don’t let these helpless cars be thrown into these arenas when they should be in a nursing garage. help us rescue them! please from now i beg you to use the #me3 hashtag on your posts and i urge you to get behind this cause. cars are more than a means to a destination. they hurt. they love. they matter #me3

text: read the comment below and you will see the song in a different light.. hilarious though it will continue to be.. but 👇 @regran_ed from @faraz_waqar -  #metoo in pakistan 1970s 😂👍 - hilarious. this video will make you laugh till your stomach hurts. the 'me too' movement did not gather much steam in pakistan vs neighbouring india in 2018. however more than 40 years ago, in the 1970s this super hit pakistani film 'shabana' (1976) addressed the issue of women being sexually harassed at work by their male bosses. pakistani media and films were not into the 'bechari aurat'/'women are helpless victims' narrative & mindset at that time and seem to have a more progressive approach to the subject. the heroine in the movie proactively deals with her evil boss, who regularly gets female office staff drunk at office parties to abuse & molest them. instead of falling victim to his evil plans, she tries to strangle him, shoots at him with a gun, & slaps the living day lights out of him. 😂😂 the entire film is about fighting off these unwelcome advances by men at the workplace. the movie created a box office record and completed more than 100 weeks at the cinemas in 1976. #metoo #metoopakistan #1970s #karachi #karachicityoflights #pakistan #citybythesea - #regrann

text:
equilibrium
--
you didn't just leave. 
i had to erase you from my mind
from my fingers and bones,
from my cracked ribs that held a broken heart, still beating...
.
.
.
you didn't just leave, 
you made me fight with every thought of yours,
every voice inside my head was your voice... .
.
.
you didn't just leave, you made me your shadow! 
i had to look for me, 
i was buried deep under the piles of your garbage words that i allowed in. 
how could i ever believe you? .
.
oh! why didn't you just leave
with all your belongings? 
why do i have to keep cleaning up after you.
one  piece of letter here, one cloth there, some thoughts on the floor, some on the ceiling.
.
.
why the hell did you not just leave,
 forever, at once?
you left in waves...
and sometimes i still see bits of you.
.
.
but you know what,
my crests and troughs are becoming smaller and smaller. 
i am about to reach equilibrium 
and your voices, your thoughts, your energies, your visions will just be something i lived through.
.
.
and i am going to be grateful for this, 
yes, i am going to one day look back and realise, you were my gift, my turning point, my decider for the road less traveled and my tipping point! .
. ~
zenona
..
------
i once fell as if i will never rise but i did rise and now i know the way to show my fellow fallers! 
remember it's okay to fall. but its not okay to stay there! 
get up! move along... don't crowd the road. there are others behind you that need you to keep moving! .
.

vocês não estão sozinhas!

text: “i’m very pleased and proud to loan a piece of my artwork to @ymcanorfolk stepping stones cafe in norwich today. art has provided me a way in which to tackle some very difficult and dark moments in my life. and i hope that people visiting stepping stones can look at my work and find a glimmer of hope in whatever struggles they may be facing themselves. for me, it’s never been about just selling paintings. but about providing hope to those who feel lost and alone. after 14 years i’ve finally found my ‘voice’. i hope everyone visiting and working at stepping stones finds theirs.” - jamie. #art #artist #abstract #abstractart #creative #visualarts #norfolk #norwich #ymca #ymcanorfolk #charity #depression #mentalhealth #metoo #norfolkart #norfolkartist #raw #energy #emotionalcontent #artoninstagram #artchangesthings #thinkdifferent #paint #acrylic #canvas #artiststakerisks

text:
[read caption below 👇]
.
you know what's wrong? doing something wrong and thinking its cool, because there's no guilt, for the only reason that boys don't think about it. and today i'm specifically talking about boys.
-
so i was playing with couple of randoms and they were having a talk about some girl. they were like, i wish she was here, would have fucked her.
-
i have no shame in bringing out what many boys talk about, but i do feel sorry for the double standards we show.
let another guy talk like that about our sister and we will kill that guy, is what we say.
-
a girl, is a human like you, has a body like you and emotions like you, and she is being treated like nothing but a sex object by one else than you. that single statement defines your ethics, morality and values, the person you are and what you think.
-
it means nothing by sharing "respect girls" quotes on facebook and instagram if this is what you think about any girl.
-
me, as a guy, take a pledge to change this thing about my friends. i will stop them from talking such things about any girl, known or unknown.
.
slowly, i hope things will change, the words will change and maybe someday the views will also change.
.
tag your friends and take a pledge today so that each one of you could proudly save that i brought a change!
.
.

text:
blame abuser not neo tantra

i’ve been thinking a lot of what is going on in the tantra community and i am frustrated at the fact that some people are trying to blame neo tantra for all the abuse and rapes in tantra. i don’t see it that way. i see it as people, individuals whether they are in or out of tantra, they are the ones responsible for their actions.

so many want to blame anyone or anything but the people that are responsible. like my mother who wanted to blame herself because of some abuse i went through when i was young…she blamed herself, when i told her it wasn’t her fault she said “then why did you let it happen”? she couldn’t conceive that this wasn’t hers or my fault, that it was the person who did the abuse.

well it is not tantra’s fault for the abuse. it is an easy way to get people naked and then abuse people. but it is not tantra, it is the practitioners themselves. when i look at the list of people who have been much of the abuse in the tantra world, they have some association with source school of tantra. that makes sense as when the owner of a school crosses boundaries, and many follow suit. and, not all have. i know many students from them who haven’t crossed boundaries, though many of those are women, and i have known women from source that have gone beyond what we are taught and shown in our training. and i know people from other schools and lineages that cross boundaries and abuse, so it is not all source too. 
i will take a guess that people do this as it has been done to them in a session with a teacher or they had it in them anyway. abuse and prostitution is not part of tantra, it is rape or prostitution. or it is being a sex surrogate, but again, that is not tantra. and i am not against prostitution or sex surrogacy, i am against people saying they are doing tantra but what they really are doing is something else…hand jobs, release, sex surrogacy or prostitution. just call it what it is, don’t put it under the guise of “tantra”. i spoke to one of the main assistants at source tantra a few years ago and she said “i don’t know how you can not have sex with your clients, i just don’t know 
cont below
#metoo #metoowithdakas #tantra

text: “i’m very pleased and proud to loan a piece of my artwork to @ymcanorfolk stepping stones cafe in norwich today. art has provided me a way in which to tackle some very difficult and dark moments in my life. and i hope that people visiting stepping stones can look at my work and find a glimmer of hope in whatever struggles they may be facing themselves. for me, it’s never been about just selling paintings. but about providing hope to those who feel lost and alone. after 14 years i’ve finally found my ‘voice’. i hope everyone visiting and working at stepping stones finds theirs.” - jamie. #art #artist #abstract #abstractart #creative #visualarts #norfolk #norwich #ymca #ymcanorfolk #charity #depression #mentalhealth #metoo #norfolkart #norfolkartist #raw #energy #emotionalcontent #artoninstagram #artchangesthings #thinkdifferent #paint #acrylic #canvas #artiststakerisks

text:
#metoo .
————-
“so i always grew up thinking that if a man ever harassed me, i would make a huge fuss about it, report him, hit back, make a public scene, something of the sort. when i did none of those, i was more shocked at my inability to stand up for myself and speak about it than anything else. along with feelings of anger, sadness and shame, i also felt i had betrayed myself. i am someone belonging to a relatively privileged background financially, i am aware of my rights, i would have ‘contacts’; (because we all know how important that is) and yet i didn’t do anything. if i couldn’t stand up for myself, how could i expect any other girl who faces a similar situation, if not much worse, every day to do it. this social system of patriarchy, i realized, is bigger than i thought it was, and the following narration is my small attempt to raise a voice against it.”
———————————————————————

text: jag hatar inte män. däremot hatar jag det många män gör och utsätter kvinnor för. jag hatar hur de dessutom förminskar och förlöjligar övergreppen och problemen, hur de håller varandra om ryggen och pratar om drev och mobbning när offer vägrar vara tysta om sådant de blivit utsatta för. jag hatar hur många män, likt katten på bilden, medvetet eller omedvetet sätter sig på och trycker ner kvinnor. hur de står tysta utan att ingripa när de ser eller hör kvinnor bli nedvärderade och trampade på. jag hatar även att det finns kvinnor som märkligt nog väljer att misstro och håna kvinnor som har modet att stå upp och säga stopp. som berättar om hur verkligheten för många flickor och kvinnor ser ut. en verklighet jag tyvärr vet att min dotter kommer ställas öga mot öga med. jag kan bara hoppas att hon blir lindrigt utsatt och inte tillhör den alltför stora grupp som drabbas å det grövsta. jag kan bara prata om det, stötta och bygga hennes självförtroende och styrka. resten är upp till männen. jag ber till alla makter att de ska välja en respektfull väg istället för den sviniga, vidriga väg som de män vars handlingar jag hatar väljer. #metoo #nomorefuckstogive #inteallamän #hatarhandlingarna #tryggatjejer #starkatjejer #vågagörakinnorsrösterhörda

text:
joan crawford visiting myrna loy on the set of 'man-proof' with j. edgar hoover and clyde tolson, 1938.
.
an excerpt from loy's autobiography being and becoming:

bob mcintyre gave me a consolation prize, a job in pretty ladies. that's when i first met joan crawford. we were both chorus girls in this thing, which starred zasu pitts and tom moore and featured norma shearer, conrad nagel, and a lot of people impersonating ziegfeld follies stars. it's amazing to think that norma, joan, and i would all become rather important to mgm in later years. and here we were, joan and i these two little extras, as part of a human chandelier. they had us hanging on to this thing with our toes out, all of these girls going in different directions. it was a riot.

joan had been signed to a contract, and she was living on nothing but black coffee to slim down for the camera. she was still lucille le sueur then. they ran a contest after pretty ladies to find her a new name. oh, she was wonderful! she was learning all the new dances, black bottom, charleston, and urging me to go down to the ambassador and do them with her. being such a snob about dance, of course, i wouldn't have any part of it. but that's what made her a star, later on, in our dancing daughters.

one day, joan came into the dressing room looking very unhappy. she fell into my lap - and she began to cry. joan always worried terribly. i did, too, but never showed it. apparently, harry rapf, the producer who discovered her, had chased her around the desk the night before. she was having a terrible time. she had such a beautiful body that they were all after her. i didn't have quite that much trouble - my sort of snooty attitude put them off a bit.
.
↪️#joanmetrogoldwynmayer

text:
consent. it’s a powerful word that, for some bizarre reason, is still argued about to this day. it seems many people still don’t really get what “consent” means:||it must be an “enthusiastic yes”. the mere fact that someone doesn’t say “no” when touched does not mean they consent. they might be afraid, asleep or too drunk to say no. ||it must be ongoing for as long as the sexual activity continues. just because i said yes to having sex this morning doesn’t mean i want sex this afternoon. just because i said yes to kissing doesn’t mean i agree to continue on to having intercourse.||it must be mutual. ||it must freely given, voluntarily, when the person’s judgment is not impaired. alcohol or drugs, being asleep or too young to understand, all of these nullify a yes. if someone says yes when they are drunk, it’s not consent.||people don't have to explain why they were there that late, or had those many drinks, or what they were wearing. it appears that “no” is only a “no” if it is under unique circumstances, all of which are constantly changing to protect the perpetrator.
《consent aint so complex . just ask》#consent #feminism #metoo #hearmetoo #equality #women #prochoice  #rapeculture #bodypositivity #womensrights #activism #gay #respect #boundaries #important #girlpower #sexl #sexualhealth #roadtochange  #abuse #recovery #marchforourlives #freedom #power #transrights #peace #lesbian #sexeducation

text: #metoo in pakistan 1970s 😂👍 - hilarious. this video will make you laugh till your stomach hurts. the 'me too' movement did not gather much steam in pakistan vs neighbouring india in 2018. however more than 40 years ago, in the 1970s this super hit pakistani film 'shabana' (1976) addressed the issue of women being sexually harassed at work by their male bosses. pakistani media and films were not into the 'bechari aurat'/'women are helpless victims' narrative & mindset at that time and seem to have a more progressive approach to the subject. the heroine in the movie proactively deals with her evil boss, who regularly gets female office staff drunk at office parties to abuse & molest them. instead of falling victim to his evil plans, she tries to strangle him, shoots at him with a gun, & slaps the living day lights out of him. 😂😂 the entire film is about fighting off these unwelcome advances by men at the workplace. the movie created a box office record and completed more than 100 days at the cinemas in 1976. #metoo #metoopakistan #1970s #karachi #karachicityoflights #pakistan #citybythesea

text:
screenshots of a conversation between russian designer gosha rubchinskiy and a 16-year-old male fan surfaced on several social media pages this week. these screenshots show the designer asking the boy for images and telling him to take pictures in the bathroom to avoid his parents finding out. the screenshots initially appeared on @hftgroup and were  then posted across other fashion-focused accounts. the russian designer, responded by stating that it was for a casting call. however, since then the 16 year old released facetime footage, suggesting otherwise. i've read several articles and posts on this issue and it's amazing that some attempted to justify the behavior between and adult designer and a minor by saying, russian's age of consent is 16 years old. but, i believe the laws prohibit sexual pictures in russia.
gosha is known for bringing youth culture and has featured russian teens in several of his fashion shows. in the us because of documented child sexual abuse (csa), we have underage modeling laws. one is the models’ harassment protection act, which was introduced by a former child model. however in other countries laws are minimal & have a lot of grey areas. this topic was brought to the forefront during the #metoo movement by several fashion ppl, of which many were unsure if anything could be done in the fashion industry. how do we protect these teens in fashion? 
as i stated before, speaking to your children and even learning about sexual health as an adult, can be a protection against sexual abuse and improving your sexual health. those who have or had a csa history have greater risk of experiencing more adverse outcomes, including risky sexual behaviors, sexual problems, and negative sexual self-concept. we must continue to speak out about sexual abuse in the fashion industries as we do in other areas. 
#preventionmeetsfashion #fashion #sexualhealth #sexeducation #socialworker #sexeducator #sexualabuse
name: FOUNDER| Nhakia Outland, MSW

text:
#przeprośkasię #stoppedofilii #stopgwałtom

gdy kilka tygodni temu przyszłyśmy na spotkanie ze stanisławem michalkiewiczem w księgarni im. jana pawła ii "sursum corda" i przeczytałam jego wypowiedź, spotkałyśmy się z olbrzymią falą nienawiści. mężczyźni krzyczeli, że jestem "cizią", że jestem za młoda, żeby cokolwiek rozumieć. próbowali mnie dotykać, odpychać. jakiś agresywny facet rzucił się na moją koleżankę, chwycił ją z całej siły za obie ręce i unieruchomił. miała po tym siniaki. to się działo na oczach dziesiątek ludzi w katolickiej księgarni, pozostały zdjęcia i filmiki. koleżanka złożyła pozew o naruszenie nietykalności cielesnej. pozew został niedawno oddalony.

i to jest kultura gwałtu. kultura gwałtu to nie tylko pojedynczy mizogin. kultura gwałtu to całe środowisko, broniący go ludzie, brak reakcji, machina prawna. michalkiewicz sam nic nie znaczy. a jednak publikuje książki i przyjeżdża na spotkania. ktoś te książki wydaje, ktoś te spotkania organizuje. ktoś na te spotkania przychodzi. gdyby nie to, jego wypowiedzi przestałyby funkcjonować publicznie, a on szybko by zniknął. a kasia nie usłyszałaby jego obrzydliwych słów.

wszyscy jesteśmy odpowiedzialni za to, co robimy i wybieramy - i w jakim świecie żyjemy. nasze wspólne działania naprawdę mają konsekwencje. niedawno michalkiewicz miał mieć spotkanie w radiu emaus. dzięki naszemu oporowi spotkanie zostało odwołane.

dlatego nie zgadzajmy się na publiczne celebrowanie mizoginów i seksistów. to nie są społeczne autorytety ani "kontrowersyjni" komentatorzy. nie ma nic antysystemowego w uporczywym powtarzaniu tego, co słychać od lat, do znudzenia - w usprawiedliwianiu sprawców przemocy, obwinianiu i poniżaniu ofiar.

my mamy swoje autorytety - nie są nimi mizogini, antysemici i faszyści. mamy swoje bohaterki. i będziemy je wspierać. naszą bohaterką jest kasia. dzięki niej mamy siły do walki. dzięki niej wiele z nas odważyło się opowiedzieć swoje historie związane z przemocą seksualną i zawalczyć o siebie. opowiedzieć swojej matce, przyjaciółce, siostrze, córce. synowi. syn stanisława michalkiewicza przeprosił za słowa ojca. jego ojciec wciąż tego nie zrobił.

text:
let’s try this again. ig removed my last one because apparently nipples are offensive. 🤷‍♀️ in greek mythology, medusa was a victim of rape who ended up becoming a monster. the myth can be seen as a parallel to the tragic experience that is had by victims of sexual assault and violence. like medusa, women who experience this suffer the betrayal, psychological and physical violation, and misplaced blame for the crimes that are committed against them. but also like medusa, they carry within themselves the ability to rise above these violations and attacks; to draw on their strength and live a life centered on creative renewal instead of destruction.
.
.

text:
что в этом году будет трендом за океаном?
⠀
ставь лайк💓, и читай про крутые тренды 2019 года!
⠀
2018-й стал годом движения #metoo и целой серии протестов против сексуального насилия в америке🇺🇸. популярные тренды сезона — кожа и анималистичные принты — призваны защищать женщин от агрессивного мира, а надписи на футболках — нести политическое послание.
⠀
кожа💣
один из главных трендов прошлого сезона остается популярным и сейчас: в кожу одеваются с ног до головы. в моде плащи, платья, юбки и пиджаки из нее. 
в наступившем сезоне этот материал может быть всех цветов и текстур.
⠀
анималистические принты🐯
традиционные леопардовые принты немного изменили свою окраску — стали синими, зелеными, желтыми. леопард меняет не только цвет, но и текстуру: пятна дизайнеры разбрасывают по ткани произвольно.
⠀
желтый цвет👑
накануне открытия недели моды в нью-йорке институт цвета pantone назвал модные цвета сезона осень-зима — 2018/19. их опять 10, и желтый — один из самых популярных цветов сезона, причём оттенки варьируются от ярко-желтого до янтарного.
⠀
слоганы на футболках🆓
популярный в 70-е годы тренд вернулся! популярная тема — права животных. например, компания lacoste выпустила футболки с логотипами вымирающих видов, выручка от продажи которых пошла на их спасение.
⠀
бельевой стиль👗
платья с кружевами на тоненьких бретельках, напоминающие комбинацию, делают из шелка, хлопка и даже кожи.
⠀
кроссовки👟
их носят с платьями, юбками, брюками, классическим пальто. белые кроссовки остаются на пике моды, так как они сочетаются буквально со всем.
новый зимний тренд — кроссовки нежных пастельных оттенков: сиреневые, персиковые и бледно-розовые.
⠀
сумка на ремне👜
поясные сумки стали еще более стильными и удобными.
⠀
#мода #лук #стиль #look #style #образ #сапоги #trends2019 #кроссовки #кожа #футболка #сумканапояс #эпиляция  #epilage #epilageoriginal  #депиляция #депиляциявоском #epilageplaceсовет

film yang kental dengan isu perempuan di masyarakat ini juga menggambarkan seseorang yang bimbang akan pilihannya hidupnya. lalu bagaimanakah kelanjutan kisah siti? saksikan hanya di enam belas film festival bali pada closing night, yang akan dimeriahkan oleh acoustic performance dari penyanyi dan penulis lagu berdarah filipina-amerika @sandrayatifay diikuti penampilan teater oleh @teaterkalangan.

hari: senin, 10 desember 2018
jam: registrasi dibuka pukul 16.00 wita
venue: cushcush gallery, jalan teuku umar gg. rajawali 1a, denpasar

festival ini gratis dan jangan lupa membawa tumbler/botol sendiri, karena acara ini berkomitmen zerowaste.

sampai jumpa di closing night #enambelasffestbali!

text: this is my story of how i am overcoming toxic relationships and reclaiming my life- spirituality, mentally, emotionally, and physically. people often wonder why some repeat negative cycles in relationships. many don’t know about the actual physical reasons people unknowingly repeat cycles and the daily persistence it takes to overcome this destructive behavior. additionally, as a childhood sexual abuse survivor, i all too often hear, “well why didn’t she tell?” the reality is that some of us have told those we felt should most have believed us. however, we have left even more hurt by the person we told response (or non-response). we also may not tell out of fear, learned behavior/grooming, or internalized self-hate. this insta story is part of a youtube series i’m doing on what lead to my 30+ years dance with toxic relationships (family, relatives, friends, and intimate partners) and how i survived them. my story is designed to help others in their journey to mental health and self-love. 🖤

text:
me too, with you : 티제와 로니에가 청소 시간에 늦는 것을 보고 키리토와 유지오는 불안을 느낀다, 그러던 중 페르니카가 찾아와 그들의 소식을 알려주었고 자신이 운벨과 라이오스에게 성폭행을 당한 것을 고백한다... 그러자 분노한 유지오는 곧바로 그들의 방으로 찾아가 그들을 추궁하고 역시나... 그들은 티제와 로니에에게 자신들의 권위를 이용하여 성폭행을 저지르고 있었다... 라이오스는 그에게 네가 나에게 검을 대면 금기목록 위반이라며 겁박하지만 그는 그것에 굴하지 않고 자신의 한쪽 눈을 대가로 운벨의 팔을 잘라낸다, 그러자 라이오스가 그를 죽이려 하고 곧이어 나타난 키리토가 라이오스의 팔을 잘라내고 그는 얼마 못 가 죽는다... 하지만 운벨은 살아있었다... 그렇게 사태가 해결되나 했더니... 또 다시 동굴에서 본 얼굴이 나타나고 알 수 없는 말을 지껄인다, 이후 유지오는 아즈리카의 마법으로 잃었던 눈을 되찾는다, 그리고 키리토와 유지오는 성장하여 정합기사가 된 앨리스와 마주하게 되는데...
p.s 팔이 아니라 다리를 잘랐어야... 그리고 라이오스랑 운벨은 xx 잘라서 토치로 그슬려야...
#소드아트온라인앨리시제이션 #10화 #권위를이용한성폭력 #metoo #metoowithyou #미투 #미투운동 #미투위드유 #나는불꽃이다 #정의구현 #앨리스 #애니리뷰 #애니스타그램 #덕스타그램

text:
i too have a story to share.

this one's is about the woman i started following on instagram. natasha noel. @natashanoel001 .
.
she's a motivational speaker and also a yogini. her posts and videos are exactly what every human who is broken somewhere from inside needs to hear desperately. her words are so powerful and inspiring, that just a small video or reading the caption of any of her random post makes me feel more confident about myself. and what's more amazing is that she herself is healing. she herself is a survivor of childhood abuse.

she is a live example of the beautiful quote - "you can be both a masterpiece and a work in progress simultaneously." keep smiling and wish you loads of happiness in life. .
- from swarada @d_arcane_pneuma
.
.
.................................................................
.

in these times of #metoo and stories of sexual harassment, there are also women and men around us who made us feel more beautiful, more confident and powerful from both inside and out. 
if there is such a person in your life who ever made you feel so about yourself then wait no longer and share your story too. let us pay a small tribute to her/him here @shespeaksforthechange.

we all need such people around us afterall, don't we?
(dm us your story or tag us in your post.) _______________________________________

#yogini #loveyourself #inspiration #motivation

text: since add cabaret is sold out tonight (we’ve added a 2nd show a week from tonight on the 16th! ❄️tix link in bio!) i thought i would give the gift of leah’s jew friendly christmas windows on grand street!  this year’s effort is rushed and phoned in as is leah’s signature style- but it seems there is a potential #metoo moment about to happen with the meth eyes snowman and the little reindeer looking just as dazed and drugged up.  yikes- harvey weinstein much? because of the jewish population in these neck of the woods, leah gives hanukkah one of the 3 window panels and the lack of attention to the detail of this menorah makes me want to snore-a.  then again details seem to evade leah’s paintings like dump truck on tiffany’s birthday. 😖the final and only good thing i have to say about these horrendous holiday windows is the touch of satanic majesty in leah’s “m”s as seen in the final picture.  there’s a mephistopheles kind of feel that i like!  there you have it folks!  merry christmas 🎄 happy hanukkah and hail satan from leah’s holiday windows!  #holidaywindows #windowpainting #ghettogrocery #attentiondeficitdisordercabaret #addcabaret #leahdoesitagain #windowfail #holidayfail #hailsatan

@warif_ng we salute & thank you 4 all you do 4 d abused.

@regran_ed from @warif_ng -  day 15 | december 09 because we have accepted to hide the abuse we suffer, because we have decided to be silent through the hurt. because we don’t speak loud enough or often enough. because of the fear, the tears and the stares. but no more! 
it is time to hear me too, it is our time to stand up and fight against any abuse or violation of any girl, woman or child. we will no longer sit still and be silent. 
we will honour ourselves by standing up and speaking as we take back our power.

the time is now. it is time for change!

share our stories, repost, tag someone and join us in the #orangetheworldwithwarif campaign as we participate in the #16daysofactivism against gender based violence.

text:
на что можно сходить на этой неделе.
⠀
🍍вдовы - жены грабителей разбираются
 с проблемами своих мужчин после их внезапной гибели. у фильма есть как минимум два привлекающих момента - это стив маккуин в режиссерском кресле и выдающаяся артистка виола дэвис в главной роли. вы, наверняка, помните её по "прислуге". на уровне сюжета всё выглядит как мрачная версия "восьмерки
оушен", на практике, скорее всего, будет развлекательный фильм с уклоном в феминистскую повестку. "вдовы" - наиболее мейнстримная картина в этом списке, но, в конце концов, как часто удается посмотреть остросюжетное кино, центральными персонажами которого являются женщины?
⠀
👾жена - современный парафраз истории колетт, фильм о которой тоже скоро выйдет в россии. джоан всю жизнь сочиняет книги за мужа, и уже настрочила на нобелевскую премию, но супруг и не думает признавать её авторство. если судить чисто по трейлеру, "жена" - это крик души, состоящий из сплошных клише абьюза и угнетения. с другой стороны, гленн клоуз абы в чем не снимается да и остальной каст хороший.
⠀
🐲нация убийц - провокационная и кровавая интерпретация "охоты на ведьм" в современном салеме. четыре школьницы
 берутся за оружие, чтобы не стать жертвами разъяренной толпы, помешавшейся на интернете. кибербуллинг, приватность в цифровую эпоху, #metoo и другие тревоги современной массовой культуры плюс немного старого-доброго ультранасилия. звучит очень привлекательно.
⠀
на oddly.sexy то же самое, но с трейлерами.
⠀
#вдовы_фильм #женафильм #нацияубийц #фемкино #киноновинки

text:
«здравствуйте, татьяна! мой вопрос такой: как вы считаете, чем именно вызван всплеск сексизма в россии в последние несколько лет? я и мои подруги ощутили за период с 2010-го волны нарастающего осуждения и ненависти к нам как к женщинам даже со стороны семьи, люди как с цепи сорвались. что же происходит на самом деле?»
___________
⠀
привет! я не вижу всплеска сексизма, все примерно так, как раньше было, причем раньше бывало и хуже.
⠀
скажем, сейчас куча народу не удивляется, если ты не красишься, не носишь лифчик, занимаешься «мужской» работой, требуешь свои алименты через суд, не делая вид, что ты выше этого, не пытаешься прикинуться няшей, когда от тебя этого ждут на голом месте, не бежишь мыть посуду за милыми мальчиками в офисе, не хихикаешь, когда тебя называют украшением коллектива, или ходишь без каблуков. да, спокойной реакции на это немного, но куда больше, чем 20 или 30 лет назад.
⠀
думаю, сейчас не всплеск сексизма, а наша чувствительность к нему повысилась, мы начали его замечать, выявлять и обсуждать. у нас появились площадки, где мы можем говорить об этом, появился язык обсуждения, мы ощутили поддержку подруг и начали посылать подальше тех, кто пытается отвоевать свое. соцсети свое дело сделали — каждый яркий случай широко обсуждается.
⠀
но это не значит, что сексизма стало больше, просто у нас наконец-то открылись на него глаза. ближайшие годы станут сложными, потому что каждая начнет замечать все больше и больше всего, с кем-то придется поссориться из-за этого и что-то потерять. но увидеть реальность такой, какая она на самом деле, сверхценно.
⠀
#никонова_ответ
