«здравствуйте, татьяна! мой вопрос такой: как вы считаете, чем именно вызван всплеск сексизма в россии в последние несколько лет? я и мои подруги ощутили за период с 2010-го волны нарастающего осуждения и ненависти к нам как к женщинам даже со стороны семьи, люди как с цепи сорвались. что же происходит на самом деле?»
___________
⠀
привет! я не вижу всплеска сексизма, все примерно так, как раньше было, причем раньше бывало и хуже.
⠀
скажем, сейчас куча народу не удивляется, если ты не красишься, не носишь лифчик, занимаешься «мужской» работой, требуешь свои алименты через суд, не делая вид, что ты выше этого, не пытаешься прикинуться няшей, когда от тебя этого ждут на голом месте, не бежишь мыть посуду за милыми мальчиками в офисе, не хихикаешь, когда тебя называют украшением коллектива, или ходишь без каблуков. да, спокойной реакции на это немного, но куда больше, чем 20 или 30 лет назад.
⠀
думаю, сейчас не всплеск сексизма, а наша чувствительность к нему повысилась, мы начали его замечать, выявлять и обсуждать. у нас появились площадки, где мы можем говорить об этом, появился язык обсуждения, мы ощутили поддержку подруг и начали посылать подальше тех, кто пытается отвоевать свое. соцсети свое дело сделали — каждый яркий случай широко обсуждается.
⠀
но это не значит, что сексизма стало больше, просто у нас наконец-то открылись на него глаза. ближайшие годы станут сложными, потому что каждая начнет замечать все больше и больше всего, с кем-то придется поссориться из-за этого и что-то потерять. но увидеть реальность такой, какая она на самом деле, сверхценно.
⠀
stop_filter_tweet: « здравствуйте , татьяна ! мой вопрос такой : как вы считаете , чем именно вызван всплеск сексизма в россии в последние несколько лет ? я и мои подруги ощутили за период с 2010-го волны нарастающего осуждения и ненависти к нам как к женщинам даже со стороны семьи , люди как с цепи сорвались . что же происходит на самом деле ? » ___________ ⠀ привет ! я не вижу всплеска сексизма , все примерно так , как раньше было , причем раньше бывало и хуже . ⠀ скажем , сейчас куча народу не удивляется , если ты не красишься , не носишь лифчик , занимаешься « мужской » работой , требуешь свои алименты через суд , не делая вид , что ты выше этого , не пытаешься прикинуться няшей , когда от тебя этого ждут на голом месте , не бежишь мыть посуду за милыми мальчиками в офисе , не хихикаешь , когда тебя называют украшением коллектива , или ходишь без каблуков . да , спокойной реакции на это немного , но куда больше , чем 20 или 30 лет назад . ⠀ думаю , сейчас не всплеск сексизма , а наша чувствительность к нему повысилась , мы начали его замечать , выявлять и обсуждать . у нас появились площадки , где мы можем говорить об этом , появился язык обсуждения , мы ощутили поддержку подруг и начали посылать подальше тех , кто пытается отвоевать свое . соцсети свое дело сделали — каждый яркий случай широко обсуждается . ⠀ но это не значит , что сексизма стало больше , просто у нас наконец-то открылись на него глаза . ближайшие годы станут сложными , потому что каждая начнет замечать все больше и больше всего , с кем-то придется поссориться из-за этого и что-то потерять . но увидеть реальность такой , какая она на самом деле , сверхценно . ⠀

text:
grace brewster murray hopper (december 9, 1906 – january 1, 1992) was an american computer scientist and united states navy rear admiral.
one of the first programmers of the harvard mark i computer, she was a pioneer of computer programming who invented one of the first compiler related tools.
she popularized the idea of machine-independent programming languages, which led to the development of cobol, an early high-level programming language.
prior to joining the navy, hopper attained a ph.d. in mathematics from yale university and was a professor of mathematics at vassar college.
in 1949, she joined the eckert–mauchly computer corporation and was part of the team that developed the univac i computer.
her compiler converted english terms into machine code understood by computers.
in 1954, eckert–mauchly chose hopper to lead their department for automatic programming, and she led the release of some of the first compiled languages like flow-matic.
in 1959, she participated in the codasyl consortium, which consulted hopper to guide them in creating a machine-independent programming language.
this led to the cobol language, which was inspired by her idea of a language being based on english words.
owing to her accomplishments and her naval rank, she was sometimes referred to as "amazing grace".
the u.s. navy arleigh burke-class guided-missile destroyer uss hopper was named for her, as was the cray xe6 "hopper" supercomputer at nersc.
during her lifetime, hopper was awarded 40 honorary degrees from universities across the world.
a college at yale university was renamed in her honor.
in 1991, she received the national medal of technology.
on november 22, 2016, she was posthumously awarded the presidential medal of freedom by president barack obama.

text:
talent jumo is a passionate feminist activist from zimbabwe. a teacher by profession, talent has 13 years’ experience working on women and health programmes, particularly on sexual and reproductive health and rights, including hiv and aids. talent co-founded the young women’s leadership initiative (now katswe sistahood) in 2007, and has served katswe sistahood as director since 2012. katswe sistahood, winner of the 2015 stars global with and for girls award, has championed the agenda for movement-building with young women from marginalised communities in zimbabwe towards the achievement of their sexual and reproductive health rights. in her work, talent has prioritised rights of young women and adolescent girls from marginalised groups, including sex workers, and advocated for social protection for sexually exploited children. 
in 2016, talent was nominated to serve as the women’s representative on the country coordinating mechanism against hiv/tb and malaria, through the women’s coalition of zimbabwe- health cluster. she is a member of the women for the global fund. in 2017, talent became a member of the ngo delegation to the global fund against hiv, tb and malaria. talent is also the current chair of the right here right now (zimbabwe platform), a strategic partnership that envisions a world where young people, in all their diversity, acquire full and uninterrupted access to comprehensive sexuality education, and youth-friendly sexual and reproductive health services, including safe abortion. (words adapted from https://www.120under40.org/nominee/talent-jumo)

image: adapted from http://www.penchat.net/blog/

text_retweet:
otroligt fin bild och en värmande recension till min bok om trauma. 🌹❤️ #repost @min.bokvarld
• • • • •
vid världens ände- en bok om psykisk ohälsa efter ett trauma, skriven av jessica thåström.
•
jessica växte upp i en familj där psykisk ohälsa var en del av vardagen, en stroke i tonåren och året därpå blir hon våldtagen. riktigt traumatiska händelser som ledde till bland annat posttraumatisk stressyndrom. men är det inte bara veteraner som råkar ut för pstd? jessica vill inte längre vara en del av det sjuka utan gör allt för att bli frisk. men vägen dit är inte enkel.
•
vid världens ände är en otroligt rak och ärlig bok. fick lägga ifrån mig boken flera gånger för att läsa något annat emellanåt då den är väldigt tung att läsa. men psykisk ohälsa är inte något lätt, det är väl minst sagt något som är tungt att gå igenom. genom att läsa jessicas historia så kan det öka kunskapen kring psykisk ohälsa och skapa större förståelse. hur viktigt det är att få rätt hjälp vid dåligt mående, både av anhöriga som inom sjukvården. att aldrig förminska någons känslor och få rätt verktyg för att hantera det jobbiga. sen måste jag säga att jessica, jag beundrar dig för ditt mod till att skriva denna bok och att du har tagit dig igenom allt det jag har fått läsa om.
•
tack @jessicat.thastrom för att jag fick läsa din bok. 🙏🏼❤️

text:
hoy comparto con vosotros una ilustración muy especial 💙. cuando gerard lópez y rubén orihuela me pidieron que hiciera una ilustración de oksana kostina para su espectáculo en la gala de eukskalgym 2018, me sentí afortunada y agradecida. una colaboración maravillosa, con dos pedazos de artistas del tapiz. ¿cómo negarme a un homenaje al arte de la rítmica, inspirados por la obra del gran pablo picasso? cuando justamente eso es lo que más necesita la rítmica, artistas con ganas de contar historias, con ganas de arriesgar, de ir más allá. soy consciente de que la gala no salió como vosotros queríais, pero el viaje hasta llegar a ella, tiene un valor artístico y personal infinito. aquí estamos los de pinceladas...por más arte y por más amistad. gracias a todos los que entienden la rítmica como un arte y como una escuela de la vida, que como tal, hay que cuidar y respetar. ¡un fuerte abrazoooooo seguidores de pinceladas de rítmica!💙💙

text: min kanske viktigaste låt någonsin. aldrig har jag lagt så mycket tid och engagemang på en sång förut. den har tagit år att skriva och för första gången har jag, terese fredenwall -dyslektiker och popsnöre, skrivit ett arrangemang för stråkkvintett som ska spelas in i veckan. kanske inget stort för världen, men jag har i alla fall skrivit mitt finaste och känner mig både stolt och rörd av alla musiker som ger av sin tid för att den här låten ska få egna vingar. så varför allt detta engangemang? varför just den här låten? jag ska berätta allt, jag lovar. #mytestimony #inspelning #metoo @antonhemstrom @axelsanderssonen #närmusikentystnar #sanningenskagöraerfria

text:
i am organising an event in january that aims to demystify some of the things you may think vthe word feminism means and discuss the importance of why feminism as a movement is so important to the future of our society. 
this event is for anyone whatever understanding you already have about feminism. you may feel like all the chatter in the media about #metoo etc is confusing and doesn’t relate to you or you may feel like you have lots of ideas and thoughts that we would love to hear!

i am looking to have a panel of people willing to answer questions and talk on pre agreed topics. if you would like to contribute and/or be on the panel please let me know in the comments below. i’d particularly like to hear from women of colour, lgbtq people and women with disabilities as i feel this will give us the best opportunity to discuss a wide range of topics. don’t feel you have to be super qualified to speak. it will be a supportive environment and the main thing we want is to allow everyone who wants, to share their experiences.

we are hoping the event will take place in witney on a sunday afternoon in january (currently looking like 20th). any comments about what you’d like to hear about would also be welcome below! 
#feminism #equality #feminist #demystifyingfeminism #thiscenturyisours #intersectionalfeminism #changeforgood #womensupportingwomen #events #eventsforfeminism #discussions #wep

new rules of how to deal with female colleagues are deadly ridiculous, according to experts. however, men who did not follow the new protocol destroyed their careers.
strategy for era #metoo:
- business dinners with girls under 35 are banned
-you can not sit next to a colleague on the plane.
- rooms in hotels should be booked on different floors.
- one-on-one communication should be only with the door open, actually better to avoid it.

text:
"what if instead of drugging, shocking, tying down our mad women, we put them in warm tubs of water naked as babies and got in there with them and cooed and encouraged them to cry great salt tears, to grieve the passing of dreams, the rape of the soul? what if we rocked them to sleep in giant hammocks of competent fat arms when they were too damn exhausted with keeping up pretenses or holding up their heads any longer? what if we agreed with her that the whole world is fucking crazy, out of balance, and that she is not to blame for the halt and the lame, the lack of food, the phone not being answered, the port wine stains on babies, the wars on every continent of the globe?
what if we gave her a baseball bat (none of this nerf shit, impotent, harm none, foam battaca bat bullshit, but a solid wood bone-cracking put a goddamn lump on it base - fucking - ball bat) and let her slam every post, stump, wall, door, window, house, and car in an arena where she is cheered on to a frenzy? then let’s pick her up when she falls down exhausted and foaming and take her down to the locker room for a steam bath and a massage that leave her noodle limp and rage-less for the first time in decades.” ......and then, after she slept, and dreamt her world into being, she awoke in all her glory, adorned with jewels, sacred oils and stardust, and stood arms outstretched, face stoic, heart fierce and gave the same gift of healing to the men that love her. we're all part of the scar clan...we support eachother. #metoo #newmoonmagic #sacredmasculine #sacredfeminine #growthfromthemostunlikelyofplaces #warriorclan #medicinetribe #dark #wet #wild #messy #tangled #blessed #followtheleprechaun #thereisgoldinsideher

text:
"est ce qu on s en sort ?" comment répondre à cette femme qui pourrait être ma mère et qui doit se tenir à la rambarde pour ne pas s écrouler en osant me poser cette question après mon intervention sur mon histoire.

que dire et que faire face à ses larmes qui jaillissent de ses yeux comme si elles y étaient restées bloquer par pudeur et impuissance depuis si longtemps. 
oui on s en sort. oui si on n a pas été tuée avant, si on n a pas d enfants ou que la société les protège, nous protège.

oui on s en sort. dans quel état ? combien de temps faut il? est ce qu on est différente ? faut il se faire aider? 
si la stratégie de l agresseur est toujours la même, la réponse pénale honteusement complice parfois, lente et lourde, chaque histoire est différente, chaque reconstruction aussi pour enfin passer du statut de mort-vivante à survivante puis victorieuse. et revenir à soi.

oui on s en sort des violences conjugales, oui... #insta #instalivre #unepoulesurunmur #violencesconjugales #violencessexuelles #instamood #instabook #bookaddict #livre #femme #mumlife #superwoman #metoo #survivor

text:
“my issue is that when good men talk about bad men, they always ignore the line in the sand — the line in the sand that is inevitably drawn whenever a good man talks about bad men: “i am a good man. here is the line. there are all the bad men.” the jimmys and the good men won’t talk about this line, but we really need to talk about this line. let’s call it kevin. and let’s never call it that again. we need to talk about how men will draw a different line for every different occasion. they have a line for the locker room; a line for when their wives, mothers, daughters, and sisters are watching; another line for when they’re drunk and fratting; another line for nondisclosure; a line for friends; and a line for foes. you know why we need to talk about this line between good men and bad men? because it’s only good men who get to draw that line. and guess what? all men believe they are good. we need to talk about this because guess what happens when only good men get to draw that line? this world — a world full of good men who do very bad things and still believe in their heart of hearts that they are good men because they have not crossed the line, because they move the line for their own good. women should be in control of that line, no question.

now take everything i have said up until this point and replace “man” with “white person,” and know that if you are a white woman, you have no place drawing lines in the sand between good white people and bad white people. i encourage you to also take the time to replace “man” with “straight” or “cis” or “able-bodied” or “neurotypical,” et cetera, et cetera. everybody believes they are fundamentally good, and we all need to believe we are fundamentally good because believing you are fundamentally good is part of the human condition. but if you have to believe someone else is bad in order to believe you are good, you are drawing a very dangerous line. in many ways, these lines in the sand we all draw are stories we tell to ourselves so we can still believe we are good people.”
#hannahgadsby #notallmen #notallmenbutalotofthem #nanette #boyswillbeheldaccountablefortheiractions #endrapeculture #metoo #feminism

text:
it’s been a week of accelerated effort and commitments to end violence against women in all its forms. 
we participated at an interactive session on ending violence against women in elections. kudos to @unwomen @unwomen_africa @unwomennigeria on the launch of the programming guide on ending violence against women in elections (vawe). in pic: our head of contacts @lynongod making her contribution at the interactive discussion during the launch. 
violence against women in elections is not just a violation of the civic rights of women to vote, be voted for, or participate in the electoral process at various levels, it is a denial of their rights to be part of a free, fair and inclusive democracy. these incidents must be addressed because women’s rights are primarily human rights. -

text:
it’s been a week of accelerated effort and commitments to end violence against women in all its forms. 
we participated at an interactive session on ending violence against women in elections. kudos to @unwomen @unwomen_africa @unwomennigeria on the launch of the programming guide on ending violence against women in elections (vawe). violence against women in elections is not just a violation of the civic rights of women to vote, be voted for, or participate in the electoral process at various levels, it is a denial of their rights to be part of a free, fair and inclusive democracy. these incidents must be addressed because women’s rights are primarily human rights. -

we participated at an interactive session on ending violence against women in elections. kudos to @unwomen @unwomen_africa @unwomennigeria on the launch of the programming guide on ending violence against women in elections (vawe). violence against women in elections is not just a violation of the civic rights of women to vote, be voted for, or participate in the electoral process at various levels, it is a denial of their rights to be part of a free, fair and inclusive democracy. these incidents must be addressed because women’s rights are primarily human rights. -

it’s been a week of accelerated effort and commitments to end violence against women in all its forms. 
we participated at an interactive session on ending violence against women in elections. kudos to @unwomen @unwomen_africa @unwomennigeria on the launch of the programming guide on ending violence against women in elections (vawe). violence against women in elections is not just a violation of the civic rights of women to vote, be voted for, or participate in the electoral process at various levels, it is a denial of their rights to be part of a free, fair and inclusive democracy. these incidents must be addressed because women’s rights are primarily human rights. -

text:
⚡️ sahkan segera rancangan undang-undang penghapusan kekerasan seksual ⚡️
.
indonesia telah gagal melindungi korban kekerasan seksual secara hukum!
. 
sejak tahun 2012, ruu p-ks hanya tergeletak di atas meja “wakil rakyat” kami di dpr, sehingga kasus-kasus seperti ibu nuril, agni, tuti trusilawati dan yang lainnya kerap bermunculan tanpa diakhiri dengan keadilan yang semestinya. menurut data @komnasperempuan, 35 orang perempuan menjadi korban kekerasan seksual setiap harinya. ini menunjukkan bahwa indonesia darurat dalam menangani kasus korban kekerasan seksual yang telah menjamur di negeri ini!
.
8 desember 2018 kemarin, bersama @sistersindanger, @simponi_id, dan banyak grup/aktivis lainnya dari berbagai kalangan (gender, ham, agamis), kami berjalan menuju depan istana untuk menuntut rancangan undang-undang penghapusan kekerasan seksual segera disahkan! #gerakbersama #metoo #hearmetoo #16haktp
.
p.s. saya tidak tergabung dengan fatayat nu, hanya memegang posternya...

text:
📢🇪🇺🎥 მეექვსე ფილმი, რომელიც ნომინირებული იყო ევროკავშირის სპეციალურ ჯილდოზე 'ადამიანის უფლებები კინოში' მარკო ტულიოს ფილმი 'ქალის სახელია', რომელიც იტალიისა და საფრანგეთის საერთო ნამუშევარია.
🎬 ფილმის იდეა 3 წლის წინ გაჩნდა და სამსახურში სექსუალურ ძალადობაზე მოგვითხრობს. მარკო ტულიოს ფილმი „ქალის სახელი" დღეს #metoo-ს ეპოქაში ამბოხების ნამდვილი მანიფესტია. ფილმი მოგვითხრობს ახალგაზრდა ქალ ნინაზე, რომელიც ქვემო ლომბარდიის პატარა სოფელში გადადის საცხოვრებლად, თავის ქალიშვილთან ერთად. ის შოულობს სამსახურს პრესტიჟულ კერძო კლინიკაში, სადაც ბევრი სხვა იტალიელი და უცხოელი ქალი მუშაობს. ქალების ეს მცირე და მრავალფეროვანი საზოგადოება, ყველაფრის მიუხედავად, ერთიანია და მათ, სხვათა შორის, საიდუმლო აერთიანებს. ისინი უფროსის მხრიდან შევიწროების მსხვერპლნი არიან, მაგრამ ამაზე ხმამაღლა არავინ საუბრობს. ნინა პირველი ქალი აღმოჩნდება, რომელიც დუმილს დაარღვევს და საკუთარი უფროსის წინააღმდეგ, ხმას ამოიღებს.
✔ ფილმის ჩვენება გაიმართება დღეს, 9 დეკემბერს, 14:00 საათზე, ამირანის კინოთეატრში. •
•
• 📢🇪🇺🎥 the sixth film to be nominated for this year's 'eu human rights in film award' is the italian/franch co-production 'woman’s name', directed by marco tullio giordana.
🎬 the film was in fact conceived over three years ago and focuses on the issue of sexual harassment in the workplace. in the era of #metoo and #timesup, and a renewed awareness of the dignity of women in the face of subversive harassment and discrimination, giordana's film arrives as a manifesto of rebellion. it's a story of nina, a young woman who moves to a small village in lower lombardy with her daughter and finds a job in a prestigious private hospital where many other women, both italian and foreign, also work. this small, ragtag community of females is nevertheless very much united - by a secret, among other things.
✔ the film will be screened today, 9 december, at 14:00, in amirani theatre.

📢🇪🇺🎥 მეექვსე ფილმი, რომელიც ნომინირებული იყო ევროკავშირის სპეციალურ ჯილდოზე 'ადამიანის უფლებები კინოში' მარკო ტულიოს ფილმი 'ქალის სახელია', რომელიც იტალიისა და საფრანგეთის საერთო ნამუშევარია.
🎬 ფილმის იდეა 3 წლის წინ გაჩნდა და სამსახურში სექსუალურ ძალადობაზე მოგვითხრობს. მარკო ტულიოს ფილმი „ქალის სახელი" დღეს #metoo-ს ეპოქაში ამბოხების ნამდვილი მანიფესტია. ფილმი მოგვითხრობს ახალგაზრდა ქალ ნინაზე, რომელიც ქვემო ლომბარდიის პატარა სოფელში გადადის საცხოვრებლად, თავის ქალიშვილთან ერთად. ის შოულობს სამსახურს პრესტიჟულ კერძო კლინიკაში, სადაც ბევრი სხვა იტალიელი და უცხოელი ქალი მუშაობს. ქალების ეს მცირე და მრავალფეროვანი საზოგადოება, ყველაფრის მიუხედავად, ერთიანია და მათ, სხვათა შორის, საიდუმლო აერთიანებს. ისინი უფროსის მხრიდან შევიწროების მსხვერპლნი არიან, მაგრამ ამაზე ხმამაღლა არავინ საუბრობს. ნინა პირველი ქალი აღმოჩნდება, რომელიც დუმილს დაარღვევს და საკუთარი უფროსის წინააღმდეგ, ხმას ამოიღებს.
✔ ფილმის ჩვენება გაიმართება დღეს, 9 დეკემბერს, 14:00 საათზე, ამირანის კინოთეატრში. •
•
• 📢🇪🇺🎥 the sixth film to be nominated for this year's 'eu human rights in film award' is the italian/franch co-production 'woman’s name', directed by marco tullio giordana.
🎬 the film was in fact conceived over three years ago and focuses on the issue of sexual harassment in the workplace. in the era of #metoo and #timesup, and a renewed awareness of the dignity of women in the face of subversive harassment and discrimination, giordana's film arrives as a manifesto of rebellion. it is a story of nina, a young woman who moves to a small village in lower lombardy with her daughter and finds a job in a prestigious private hospital where many other women, both italian and foreign, also work. this small, ragtag community of females is nevertheless very much united - by a secret, among other things.
✔ the film will be screened today, 9 december, at 14:00, in amirani theatre.

. f o r u m 🎭  jag nämnde teaterintresset här om dagen. det kändes något absurt när jag såg dokumentären om kulturprofilen på svt i onsdags och alla de kvinnor han utsatt. man fick se klipp från forum och det talades om klubben som stockholms elitscen. jag har själv stått på den scenen varje dag i flera månader men då var det långt ifrån en elitscen. bara några år tidigare, 1987, hade jag skådespeleriet som jobb och var medlem av en teatergrupp som hyrde lokalen. den hette inte forum då utan studentteatern och användes inte av någon annan än oss. jag var lite osäker på om det var samma lokal när avslöjandet om forum kom men när jag såg programmet var det ingen tvekan. det var en rätt häftig lokal och efter att ha lånat mötesrum av sthlms stad var vi glada att få ta dit vår rekvisita och sätta igång på allvar. nu är den stans mest ökända lokal. jag är så tacksam över att rättegången med stor säkerhet fått ett slut med denna utgång. en ny prövning kommer troligtvis inte beviljas enligt e. massi fritz. när det gäller vad den mannen är orsak till kan vi verkligen tala om psykiskt lidande, psykiska trauman, posttraumatiskt stressyndrom, paranoia och ångest i kubik. så mycket psykisk terror och skada kulturprofilen är orsak till finns det väl ingen annan än herr engdal som betvivlar. #metoo you know. vi som varit utsatta vet och vi är dessvärre många. .

. f o r u m 🎭  jag nämnde teaterintresset här om dagen. det kändes något absurt när jag såg dokumentären om kulturprofilen på svt i onsdags och alla de kvinnor han utsatt. man fick se klipp från forum och det talades om klubben som stockholms elitscen. jag har själv stått på den scenen varje dag i flera månader men då var det långt ifrån en elitscen. bara några år tidigare, 1987, hade jag skådespeleriet som jobb och var medlem av en teatergrupp som hyrde lokalen. den hette inte forum då utan studentteatern och användes inte av någon an än oss. jag var lite osäker på om det var samma lokal när avslöjandet om forum kom men när jag såg programmet var det ingen tvekan. det var en rätt häftig lokal och efter att ha lånat mötesrum av sthlms stad var vi glada att få ta dit vår rekvisita och sätta igång på allvar. nu är den stans mest ökända lokal. jag är så tacksam över att rättegången med stor säkerhet fått ett slut med denna utgång. en ny prövning kommer troligtvis inte beviljas enligt e. massi fritz. när det gäller vad den mannen är orsak till kan vi verkligen tala om psykiskt lidande, psykiska trauman, posttraumatiskt stressyndrom, paranoia och ångest i kubik. så mycket psykisk terror och skada kulturprofilen är orsak till finns det väl ingen an än herr engdal som betvivlar. #metoo you know. vi som varit utsatta vet och vi är dessvärre många. .
.

.
.

text:
i can only speak for myself, but 30 is not the new 20. 30 is 30, and thank god for that. feeling very grateful for all the incredible adventures i've been blessed to have in my life thus far.  for whatever reasons, this is a big birthday for me. i know social media can create an image of unrealistic utopia, so i'd like to temper that with some real hard knocks i learned (the hard way) over my last 2 decades: 
1. it's ok to celebrate myself!
2. i'm manic depressive with mild ocd. feels good to say it out loud.
3. once you find the right therapist, they are worth every frickin penny. 
4. i am not required to apologize, for anything, ever. 
5. i have physical and emotional boundaries and the right to protect them. #metoo
6. it's alllll about perspective - check yo filter.
7. i will never have it all figured out.
8. i was born to sing to all of you.

what did you learn from your 20s, or what are you learning still?? tell me, i love you,  xoxo gracie

#hardknocks #grateful #30 #30thbirthday #lifelessons #chronology #birthday #rebel #culinaryschool #honduras #redhead #blondie #sisters #scubadiving #babypics

text: this is my reminder every single day that i am a survivor, not a victim. i have a story now, but it does not define me. november 11th, 2018 changed my world forever. it’s when hell all began and it’s been so scary since, the days still aren’t easy. it’s the pain, guilt, sadness, anger, consfusion, exhaustion, & injustice that take so much from me. but i can speak up & i can share the truth. i can be brave, courageous, strong, & hopeful. i can inspire people. this beautiful life can sometimes be so cruel, but i can do hard things. yes, i am a survivor. #metoo

text:
parece que o movimento #metoo aporta no brasil... aguardem, passará por celebridades, empresários, políticos e chegará ao presidente.

como?
com mentiras ora! 
é assim que funciona! 
o médium joão de deus, aquele que já atraiu personalidades famosas do mundo inteiro, está sendo acusado de assédio sexual contra um expressivo grupo de mulheres que atendeu. 
por que causa estranheza? 
vocês não acham estranho que seja exatamente igual ao modus operandi americano do movimento metoo ?

lá, na propriedade do médium, privacidade é coisa rara, o lugar está sempre lotado e ninguém nunca gritou? ninguém nunca pediu socorro? 
em 20 anos, casa lotada diariamente e só agora um bloco se reune pra gritar por socorro?... me parece difícil de acreditar. 
lembram-se do ator negro americano bill cosby? não consigo até hoje acreditar em uma única acusação.
ele era um conservador que dava palestras contra a agenda da esquerda e sua vida era a prova de suas palavras. seria casualidade que todas as suas vítimas fossem declaradamente esquerdistas? 
e por que, em todos os casos, a vítima só reclama décadas depois? 
me parece que no caso do médium, tem espírito obssessor nas vítimas e não no possível agressor. um espírito safado, cheio de dinheiro e projeção social e midiática movido por interesses políticos. 
um alvo inesperado, onde a opinião pública é pega de surpresa, num país ainda católico, com o protestantismo como segunda religião, tendo todos horror à crença de joão de deus, não é dificil ganhar a simpatia da população. 
não esquecendo que a violência sexual é desde sempre uma eficaz arma política,  sendo usada mesmo em guerras, raciocinar que outras vítimas se sentirão encorajadas a lutar por justiça (vejam que o discurso quase convence) e a onda de reclamações e justiçamento anti-machista se espalhará, alcançará os nomes mais improváveis, é apenas um desenvolvimento lógico. 
não por acaso esse alarme é soado pela rede globo - a mesma que engendra os  fenômenos psico-sociais no brasil.

aguardemos e veremos a panela do #elenão aderir ao #metoo.

será que no brasil chamarão de #eutambém ?

de todo modo, para joão de deus é  irrelevante. ele, que não é o alvo central

text: now. the timbers you see hold up the third and fourth floors of my condo. they are strong, much like i am. earlier this week a professional asked me if i had a pimp. thrown off for just a second i answered no, but as i think about the question more, perhaps i did. i’ve asked a number of people if they’d like to look at the porn that i’m in and the look on their face or the sound of their voice in response is something of nervous shock. i say it’s ok, i’m drugged and am being raped, but that usually doesn’t change things for them. the people behind turning me into porn have done a very good job of scrubbing the internet clean of it. i still stick to my original premise though of once on the internet always on the internet. and i’m prepared for the horror that you have done to me. after all, i’ve already lived it.

text:
happy weekend!

when it was first published, fat is a feminist issue became an instant classic and it is as relevant today as it was then. reflecting on our increasingly diet and body-obsessed society, susie orbach’s new introduction explains how generations of women and girls are growing up absorbing the eating anxieties around them. in an age where women want to be sexy, nurturing, domestic goddesses, confident at work, and feminine too, the twenty-first-century woman is poorly armed for survival. never before has the fat is a feminist issue revolution been more in need of revival.

exploring our love/hate relationship with food, susie orbach describes how fat is about so much more than food. it is a response to our social situation; the way we are seen by others and ourselves. too often food is a source of anguish, as are our bodies. but fat is a feminist issue discusses how we can turn food into a friend and find ways to accept ourselves for who and how we are. following the step-by-step guide, and you too can put an end to food anxieties and dieting.

text:
(parte i) normalmente no soy una persona muy privada. me gusta tener el corazón abierto, y cuando alguna historia mía pueda servirle a alguien más entonces la comparto. aún así mantengo mis propios secretos bajo llave. no en esta ocasión. 
yo tenía 16 años y se me hacía tarde para un examen así que salí a toda velocidad en la madrugada a tomar el camión. estaba obscuro y la calle vacía, cuando escuché a alguien corriendo de tras mío. 
miré hacia atrás y a lo lejos pude ver un hombre a toda prisa y como un león que ha encontrado a su presa cambió su rumbo repentina y velozmente hacia mi. apresuré el paso pero en un parpadeo lo tuve de frente mío amenazándome con un cuchillo. me pidió mi bolso pero, qué podría traer que le interesara? nada excepto una cosa. 
yo era una niña y no conocía hombre hasta ese momento, pero él me tomó del hombro y me llevó donde los faroles de la calle no alumbraban para cambiar eso. 
me tocaba en formas que yo sentía asco y sentía que se me iba la vida. 
cuando terminó conmigo me arrodilló al suelo y me pidió que no mirara y así como si nada se fue... ...yo era una niña, tirada en la obscuridad. violentada y robada de lo más precioso que tenemos los seres humanos. me tomó un largo tiempo parar de llorar. sentía que la noche me tragaba y el miedo de que él volviera era terrible. no podía  moverme, ni siquiera respirar. me tomó lo que para mi fue una eternidad volver a casa, derrotada, con el alma mutilada. rompí en llanto en cuanto la puerta cerró de tras de mi que desperté a todos. 
mi vida continuó, con algunos tropiezos pero lo logré. y sobrevivo al recuerdo constantemente y no hay ocasión que no lo cuente con la cara chorreada y la voz cortada. pero sobreviví. y no soy la primera ni la ultima. no soy lo que me pasó, no soy mi atacante y no soy la víctima de nadie. #yoga #cdmx #yogalifestyle #swag #instacool #tweegram #progress #yogagirl #yogateacher #igers #yogagram #igersmexico #follow #picoftheday #webstagram #instadaily #20likes #all_shots #instagramers #yogapractice #yoga_feature #yogalifestyle #lifestyle #instagood  #igyogacommunity #practiceyogachangeyourworld #onebreathatatime #metoo #metoomovement

text: 🛑 i think it’s about time i apologize to the girl on the left. i let her endure more pain than anyone should ever go through. forcing smiles through narcissism, physical abuse, sexual abuse and feeling like she wasn’t worth any more than the speck of dirt stuck to gum on the bottom of her shoe. 💪🌟👏 that woman on the right though, she fought those battles, she grew from those battles, does she have scars? yep. does she have vivid flashback dreams? absolutely. but she is strong, she is brave, she has learned to love herself, to give love selflessly and to be loved. she’s found herself, she’s found her place, she’s genuinely happy. ⁉️this post isn’t about attention, i just want other women to know, there is life after hardships, and if anyone of you needs a friend through any of the above scenarios, i am here. i will be your shoulder to cry/lean on, be the neutral and logical voice in your head. i’ll be your pusher when you want to give up, because at the end of the day, everyone 100% deserves to feel, to be loved, to be respected, to feel strong, to know they will always survive, the way the woman pictured on the right does. #imamermaid #selflove #oilymama #yleo #woman #chickswithtattoos #womenwithtattoos #piercings #metoo

text:
jag har noterat att många kollegor är upprörda över svt:s val av mikael persbrandt som nyårstalare på nyårsafton. jag har full respekt för de kritiska rösterna och att de har åsikter om hur han har betett sig tidigare i sin karriär mot dem och andra som motsäger sig detta. 
men jag tycker samtidigt i hela denna #metoo debatt att vi måste kunna ge utrymme för att släppa fram människor som faktiskt har hittat en bättre väg i livet och som i detta fall fått vård för sin diagnos och sitt beroende. ingen människa kan bli straffad på livstid, mord undantaget. jag tycker mikael har gjort en fantastisk resa som har hittat tillbaka till livet, till ett bättre liv hoppas jag. det måste vi kunna få hylla också, jag tycker iallafall att det är fint och storartat med människor som hittar rätt i livet. det finns så många tråkiga och tragiska exempel på människor som inte har lyckas med det. jag ser fram emot att få höra dig läsa "ring klocka ring" på nyårsafton mikael. @mikaelpersbrandtofficial 🙏🏼✨#svt #mikaelpersbrandt

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the fake content - there is no way they are going to risk their business by taking a real responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words, every day.

the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and keep abusing the faith of their fellow men. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

dear america, me me me finnish ass can't do more than this.

text:
it has been heavy on my heart to share about respect. specifically in the realm of speaking out... our culture is very aware of #metoo #timesup #whyididntreport and #womensreality 
i always have admiration for these people who have been directly affected by situations that would inspire them to speak out, huge respect! i never realized the impact that stepping out and sharing has. both positive and negative.
our culture is all about speaking out- bringing light to what was done and hope that through due process, justice will be found. i am a big supporter of this truth telling. i never really understood the blowback that could occur once you've made that huge step to speak out. i never fully understood the risk until i was faced with the option to speak out.
i think as humans we need to respect people. respect doesn't mean you agree. it means you honor their decision. you don't have to support, you can respect and disagree at the same time. 
in this culture of "speak out" we lack the pieces to fully support those once they do. i see people turn around and attack them instead. 
what i've experienced is people either come together and support you. completely belittle your decision and experience and disregard you, or think that their idea of what happen is truth and share your story in a negative light, taking your hardship and running it through the mud. 
i see respect a lacking pillar in humanity these days and i am heart broken. i am not sure what to do about it, because respect needs to be modeled, taught, and learned. it takes more than social media. we need pillars of hope, truth and love in our communities.... we need leaders. 
#culture #respect #speakout #truth #support #bethechangeyouwanttosee #teachthenextgeneration #raisethemstrong #ispokeout

text: el mito erótico oficial de los ochenta cumple 65 años. prejubilada, kim basinger solo sale para homenajearse a sí misma en ‘cincuenta sombras’ y, de momento, ha ignorado la llamada del #metoo. si cada generación de estadounidenses recurre a una kim para definir la sexualidad femenina —novak, basinger, kardashian—, esta kim opta hoy por dedicarse a cuidar de su hija ireland que, tras superar un tratamiento por traumas emocionales, se ha erigido como it girl y activista lgtb. y en tiempos del #metoo, basinger prefiere cerrar esa boca con la que posó entreabierta durante 10 años. si decide hablar, quizá esta vez sí habrá alguien escuchándola. en la imagen, con su entonces marido alec baldwin (getty)

"many of us were raised to say yes. we're still learning how to say no, when so often our no goes unheard." in our boundaries issue, writer ilana masad discusses the importance of communication in relationships. "in recent months, the #metoo movement has exploded into prominence. with all its issues—its focus on white, wealthy, famous women, its early erasure of the originator of the hashtag, tarana burke—it has at least caused a larger swath of the population to talk about sexual harassment, assault, and the role of power. but something we don't talk about nearly often enough is how communication sits squarely in these dynamics as well." get the full story in anxy no. 3, available via link in bio. illustration by @nalghadban

text:
dear desi contreras,
your legacy is embedded into  mrs. desirae ramirez .....
———————————————————————————
oh sweet lil mamma i have to let you know that those years of jaden memories & childhood depression did resurface. from the moment he proposed to the night you were in the er to the moment you walked down that aisle ...none of that 
was in vain.
it was needed!
as you transitioned from girlfriend to fiancé 
to
victim to survivor to wife 
mammas you were healing through it all.

yes the darkness became your friend. the darkness will always lure back in, that i will not deny.
yet, it is so ridiculously needed for a creative like you to unlock and unleash thee most marvelous art you can ever put out.
sweet desi contreras,
you wept many many nights.
went through the ring of fire 🔥 
nightmares & fear of intimacy 
with your partner and your friends.

do not be embarrassed sweet desi because i can assure you lil mamas ✨god does not waist anything ✨

text:
ah, my sweet aya necklace. ⁣
⁣
ayahuasca really reminds me of sound healing and breathwork in so many ways. aya gives you what you need. sometimes what you need and what you want aren’t aligned and you realize this after. so does breathwork and sound healing. both shed layers of ego and peel back societal expectations. you are given clarity about your own truth instead of getting lost in trying to please others. ⁣
⁣
both can let you explore your trauma with compassion and clarity so you may have the steps to move forward. it can be dark but ever so healing. the exploration is brave if nothing else. ⁣
⁣
sound healing and breathwork can personally bring me to similar realms as aya. it all depends on if i’m feeling like going off the grid for the great purge. when you feel the call, you don’t ignore it. ⁣
⁣
my prayer is for my body to be safe after what just happened. my intention is to find trust again after a deep betrayal of having my choice taken away. i want to have the courage to take what happened and use it to speak up and make change happen so that others can seek justice safely.
⁣
thank you to the #metoomovement without all of your bravery, it would be hard to find mine. ⁣
⁣
i will update post-ceremony. ⁣
⁣
aho!⁣
⁣
*peruvian aya necklace available for $50
